  <para style="toc2">Πράξεις Ἀποστόλων</para>
  <para style="toc1">ΠΡΑΞΕΙΣ ΑΠΟΣΤΟΛΩΝ</para>
  <para style="mt">ΠΡΑΞΕΙΣ ΑΠΟΣΤΟΛΩΝ</para>
  <chapter number="1" style="c" />
  <para style="s">The Promise of the Holy Spirit</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">1.1 </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="LUK 1:3">Lk 1.3</ref>
      </char>
    </note>Τὸν μὲν πρῶτον λόγον ἐποιησάμην περὶ πάντων, ὦ Θεόφιλε, ὧν ἤρξατο ὁ Ἰησοῦς ποιεῖν τε καὶ διδάσκειν, <verse number="2" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">1.2 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MRK 16:19">Mk 16.19</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 24:49-51">Lk 24.49‑51</ref></char></note>ἄχρι ἧς ἡμέρας<note caller="1" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">1.2 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{A} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἡμέρας … ἀνελήμφθη </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">74vid</char> ℵ A B C<char style="add">vid</char> E Ψ 33 81 181 307 453 610 614 945 1175 1409 1678 1739 1891 2344 2818 <char style="it">Byz</char> <char style="it">Lect</char> it<char style="add">c, dem, e, p, ph, ro, w</char> vg syr<char style="add">h</char> arm eth geo slav Basil Chrysostom Severian Nestorius ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἡμέρας ἀνελήμφθη … ἐξελέξατο καὶ ἐκέλευσεν κηρύσσειν τὸ εὐαγγέλιον </char><char style="ft" closed="false">D it<char style="add">(ar), d, (gig), (t)</char> (vg<char style="add">mss</char>) syr<char style="add">h<char style="add">mg</char></char> (cop<char style="add">sa, meg</char>) Augustine Ps-Vigilius<char style="add">2/2</char></char></note> ἐντειλάμενος τοῖς ἀποστόλοις διὰ πνεύματος ἁγίου οὓς ἐξελέξατο ἀνελήμφθη<note caller="1" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">1.2 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{A} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἡμέρας … ἀνελήμφθη </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">74vid</char> ℵ A B C<char style="add">vid</char> E Ψ 33 81 181 307 453 610 614 945 1175 1409 1678 1739 1891 2344 2818 <char style="it">Byz</char> <char style="it">Lect</char> it<char style="add">c, dem, e, p, ph, ro, w</char> vg syr<char style="add">h</char> arm eth geo slav Basil Chrysostom Severian Nestorius ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἡμέρας ἀνελήμφθη … ἐξελέξατο καὶ ἐκέλευσεν κηρύσσειν τὸ εὐαγγέλιον </char><char style="ft" closed="false">D it<char style="add">(ar), d, (gig), (t)</char> (vg<char style="add">mss</char>) syr<char style="add">h<char style="add">mg</char></char> (cop<char style="add">sa, meg</char>) Augustine Ps-Vigilius<char style="add">2/2</char></char></note>· <verse number="3" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">1.3 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">οἷς … τεκμηρίοις </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 24:36-42">Lk 24.36‑42</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 20:19-20">Jn 20.19‑20</ref>, <ref loc="JHN 20:26-27">26‑27</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">λέγων … θεοῦ </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 28:18-20">Mt 28.18‑20</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 24:46-49">Lk 24.46‑49</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 20:21-23">Jn 20.21‑23</ref></char></note>οἷς καὶ παρέστησεν ἑαυτὸν ζῶντα μετὰ τὸ παθεῖν αὐτὸν ἐν πολλοῖς τεκμηρίοις, δι᾽ ἡμερῶν τεσσεράκοντα ὀπτανόμενος αὐτοῖς καὶ λέγων τὰ περὶ τῆς βασιλείας τοῦ θεοῦ· <verse number="4" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">1.4 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">παρήγγειλεν … πατρός </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 24:49">Lk 24.49</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">τὴν ἐπαγγελίαν … μου </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="JHN 14:16-17">Jn 14.16‑17</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 15:26">15.26</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 2:33">Ac 2.33</ref></char></note>καὶ συναλιζόμενος παρήγγειλεν αὐτοῖς ἀπὸ Ἱεροσολύμων μὴ χωρίζεσθαι ἀλλὰ περιμένειν τὴν ἐπαγγελίαν τοῦ πατρὸς ἣν ἠκούσατέ μου, <verse number="5" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">1.5 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">Ἰωάννης … ἁγίῳ </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 3:11">Mt 3.11</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 1:8">Mk 1.8</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 3:16">Lk 3.16</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 1:33">Jn 1.33</ref></char></note>ὅτι Ἰωάννης μὲν ἐβάπτισεν ὕδατι, ὑμεῖς δὲ ἐν πνεύματι βαπτισθήσεσθε ἁγίῳ οὐ μετὰ πολλὰς ταύτας ἡμέρας.</para>
  <para style="s">The Ascension of Jesus</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="6" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">1.6 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">Κύριε … Ἰσραήλ </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="LUK 24:21">Lk 24.21</ref>
      </char>
    </note>Οἱ μὲν οὖν συνελθόντες ἠρώτων αὐτὸν λέγοντες, Κύριε, εἰ ἐν τῷ χρόνῳ τούτῳ ἀποκαθιστάνεις τὴν βασιλείαν τῷ Ἰσραήλ; <verse number="7" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">1.7 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">Οὐχ … ἐξουσίᾳ </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MRK 13:32">Mk 13.32</ref></char></note>εἶπεν δὲ πρὸς αὐτούς, Οὐχ ὑμῶν ἐστιν γνῶναι χρόνους ἢ καιροὺς οὓς ὁ πατὴρ ἔθετο ἐν τῇ ἰδίᾳ ἐξουσίᾳ, <verse number="8" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">1.8 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">λήμψεσθε … ὑμᾶς </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="EPH 3:16">Eph 3.16</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ἔσεσθέ μου μάρτυρες </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 24:48">Lk 24.48</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 15:27">Jn 15.27</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 2:32">Ac 2.32</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 3:15">3.15</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 5:32">5.32</ref></char></note>ἀλλὰ λήμψεσθε δύναμιν ἐπελθόντος τοῦ ἁγίου πνεύματος ἐφ᾽ ὑμᾶς καὶ ἔσεσθέ μου μάρτυρες ἔν τε Ἰερουσαλὴμ καὶ [ἐν] πάσῃ τῇ Ἰουδαίᾳ καὶ Σαμαρείᾳ καὶ ἕως ἐσχάτου τῆς γῆς. <verse number="9" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">1.9 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ταῦτα … ἐπήρθη </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MRK 16:19">Mk 16.19</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 6:62">Jn 6.62</ref></char></note>καὶ ταῦτα εἰπὼν βλεπόντων αὐτῶν ἐπήρθη καὶ νεφέλη ὑπέλαβεν αὐτὸν ἀπὸ τῶν ὀφθαλμῶν αὐτῶν. <verse number="10" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">1.10 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ἰδοὺ … λευκαῖς </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 24:4">Lk 24.4</ref></char></note>καὶ ὡς ἀτενίζοντες ἦσαν εἰς τὸν οὐρανὸν πορευομένου αὐτοῦ, καὶ ἰδοὺ ἄνδρες δύο παρειστήκεισαν αὐτοῖς ἐν ἐσθήσεσιν λευκαῖς, <verse number="11" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">1.11 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">οὗτος … πορευόμενον εἰς τὸν οὐρανόν </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 26:64">Mt 26.64</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 21:27">Lk 21.27</ref>; <ref loc="REV 1:7">Re 1.7</ref></char></note>οἳ καὶ εἶπαν, Ἄνδρες Γαλιλαῖοι, τί ἑστήκατε [ἐμ]βλέποντες εἰς τὸν οὐρανόν; οὗτος ὁ Ἰησοῦς ὁ ἀναλημφθεὶς ἀφ᾽ ὑμῶν εἰς τὸν οὐρανὸν<note caller="2" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">1.11 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{A} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">εἰς τὸν οὐρανόν </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ A B C E Ψ 81 181 307 453 610 614 945 1175 1409 1678 1739 1891 2344 2818 <char style="it">Byz</char> <char style="it">Lect</char> it<char style="add">ar, c, dem, e, p, ph, ro, t, w</char> syr<char style="add">p, h, pal</char> cop<char style="add">sa, bo, meg</char> arm<char style="add">mss</char> eth geo slav Eusebius Ps-Ignatius Epiphanius Chrysostom Proclus Theodoret<char style="add">3/4</char>; Jerome Augustine<char style="add">2/6</char> Quodvultdeus<char style="add">1/2</char> ⫽ <char style="it">omit</char> D 2495 <char style="it">l</char> 60 it<char style="add">d, gig</char> vg<char style="add">mss</char> cop<char style="add">bo<char style="add">mss</char></char> arm<char style="add">mss</char> Theodoret<char style="add">1/4</char>; Augustine<char style="add">4/6</char> Quodvultdeus<char style="add">1/2</char> Maximus Maximinus Leo Vigilius Ps-Vigilius Cassiodorus</char></note> οὕτως ἐλεύσεται ὃν τρόπον ἐθεάσασθε αὐτὸν πορευόμενον εἰς τὸν οὐρανόν.</para>
  <para style="s">The Choice of Judas’ Successor</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="12" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">1.12 </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="LUK 24:50">Lk 24.50</ref>, <ref loc="LUK 24:52">52</ref></char>
    </note>Τότε ὑπέστρεψαν εἰς Ἰερουσαλὴμ ἀπὸ ὄρους τοῦ καλουμένου Ἐλαιῶνος, ὅ ἐστιν ἐγγὺς Ἰερουσαλὴμ σαββάτου ἔχον ὁδόν. <verse number="13" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">1.13 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">Πέτρος … Ἰούδας Ἰακώβου </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 10:2-4">Mt 10.2‑4</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 3:16-19">Mk 3.16‑19</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 6:14-16">Lk 6.14‑16</ref></char></note>καὶ ὅτε εἰσῆλθον, εἰς τὸ ὑπερῷον ἀνέβησαν οὗ ἦσαν καταμένοντες, ὅ τε Πέτρος καὶ Ἰωάννης καὶ Ἰάκωβος καὶ Ἀνδρέας, Φίλιππος καὶ Θωμᾶς, Βαρθολομαῖος καὶ Μαθθαῖος, Ἰάκωβος Ἁλφαίου καὶ Σίμων ὁ ζηλωτὴς καὶ Ἰούδας Ἰακώβου. <verse number="14" style="v" />οὗτοι πάντες ἦσαν προσκαρτεροῦντες ὁμοθυμαδὸν τῇ προσευχῇ σὺν γυναιξὶν καὶ Μαριὰμ τῇ μητρὶ τοῦ Ἰησοῦ καὶ τοῖς ἀδελφοῖς αὐτοῦ.</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="15" style="v" />Καὶ ἐν ταῖς ἡμέραις ταύταις ἀναστὰς Πέτρος ἐν μέσῳ τῶν ἀδελφῶν εἶπεν· ἦν τε ὄχλος ὀνομάτων ἐπὶ τὸ αὐτὸ ὡσεὶ ἑκατὸν εἴκοσι· <verse number="16" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">1.16 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">τὴν … Ἰησοῦν </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="PSA 41:9">Ps 41.9</ref></char></note>Ἄνδρες ἀδελφοί, ἔδει πληρωθῆναι τὴν γραφὴν ἣν προεῖπεν τὸ πνεῦμα τὸ ἅγιον διὰ στόματος Δαυὶδ περὶ Ἰούδα τοῦ γενομένου ὁδηγοῦ τοῖς συλλαβοῦσιν Ἰησοῦν, <verse number="17" style="v" />ὅτι κατηριθμημένος ἦν ἐν ἡμῖν καὶ ἔλαχεν τὸν κλῆρον τῆς διακονίας ταύτης.<note caller="a" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">1.17 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">End quotation: TR WH? GNB NIV NRSV REB</char></note> <verse number="18" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">1.18 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 27:3-8">Mt 27.3‑8</ref></char></note>Οὗτος μὲν οὖν ἐκτήσατο χωρίον ἐκ μισθοῦ τῆς ἀδικίας καὶ πρηνὴς γενόμενος ἐλάκησεν μέσος καὶ ἐξεχύθη πάντα τὰ σπλάγχνα αὐτοῦ· <verse number="19" style="v" />καὶ γνωστὸν ἐγένετο πᾶσιν τοῖς κατοικοῦσιν Ἰερουσαλήμ, ὥστε κληθῆναι τὸ χωρίον ἐκεῖνο τῇ ἰδίᾳ διαλέκτῳ αὐτῶν Ἁκελδαμάχ, τοῦτ᾽ ἔστιν Χωρίον Αἵματος. <verse number="20" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">1.20 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">Γενηθήτω … αὐτῇ </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="PSA 69:25">Ps 69.25</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">Τὴν … ἕτερος </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="PSA 109:8">Ps 109.8</ref></char></note><note caller="b" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">1.20 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Begin quotation: TR WH? GNB NIV NRSV REB</char></note> Γέγραπται γὰρ ἐν βίβλῳ ψαλμῶν,</para>
  <para style="q1">
    <char style="qt">Γενηθήτω ἡ ἔπαυλις αὐτοῦ ἔρημος</char></para>
  <para style="q2">
    <char style="qt">καὶ μὴ ἔστω ὁ κατοικῶν ἐν αὐτῇ,</char></para>
  <para style="m">καί,</para>
  <para style="q1">
    <char style="qt">Τὴν ἐπισκοπὴν αὐτοῦ λαβέτω ἕτερος.</char></para>
  <para style="m">
    <verse number="21" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">1.21‑22 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">τῶν … Ἰωάννου </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="LUK 1:2">Lk 1.2</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 15:27">Jn 15.27</ref></char>
    </note>δεῖ οὖν τῶν συνελθόντων ἡμῖν ἀνδρῶν ἐν παντὶ χρόνῳ ᾧ εἰσῆλθεν καὶ ἐξῆλθεν ἐφ᾽ ἡμᾶς ὁ κύριος Ἰησοῦς, <verse number="22" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">1.22 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">τοῦ … Ἰωάννου </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 3:13-15">Mt 3.13‑15</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 1:9">Mk 1.9</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 3:21">Lk 3.21</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ἕως … ἀνελήμφθη … ἡμῶν </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MRK 16:19">Mk 16.19</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 1:9">Ac 1.9</ref></char></note>ἀρξάμενος ἀπὸ τοῦ βαπτίσματος Ἰωάννου ἕως τῆς ἡμέρας ἧς ἀνελήμφθη ἀφ᾽ ἡμῶν, μάρτυρα τῆς ἀναστάσεως αὐτοῦ σὺν ἡμῖν γενέσθαι ἕνα τούτων. <verse number="23" style="v" />καὶ ἔστησαν<note caller="3" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">1.23 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{A} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἔστησαν </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ A B C D<char style="add">1</char> E Ψ 33 81 181 307 453 610 614 945 1175 1409 1678 1739 2344 <char style="it">Byz</char> <char style="it">Lect</char> it<char style="add">ar, c, dem, e, p, ph, ro, sa, t, w</char> vg syr<char style="add">p, h</char> cop<char style="add">sa, bo, meg</char> arm eth geo slav Eusebius Basil Chrysostom ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἔστησεν </char><char style="ft" closed="false">D* <char style="it">l</char> 156 it<char style="add">d, gig</char> Augustine</char></note> δύο, Ἰωσὴφ τὸν καλούμενον Βαρσαββᾶν ὃς ἐπεκλήθη Ἰοῦστος, καὶ Μαθθίαν. <verse number="24" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">1.24 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">κύριε … πάντων </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="JHN 2:24-25">Jn 2.24‑25</ref></char></note>καὶ προσευξάμενοι εἶπαν, Σὺ κύριε καρδιογνῶστα πάντων, ἀνάδειξον ὃν ἐξελέξω ἐκ τούτων τῶν δύο ἕνα <verse number="25" style="v" />λαβεῖν τὸν τόπον<note caller="4" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">1.25 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{B} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τόπον </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">74</char> A B C* D Ψ it<char style="add">ar, c, d, dem, gig, p, ph, ro, sa, t, w</char> vg syr<char style="add">h<char style="add">mg</char></char> cop<char style="add">sa, bo, meg</char> Didymus; Augustine ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">κλῆρον </char><char style="ft" closed="false">(see <char style="xt"><ref loc="ACT 1:17">1.17</ref>)</char> ℵ C<char style="add">3</char> E 33 81 181 307 453 610 614 945 1175 1409 1678 1739 2344 <char style="it">Byz</char> <char style="it">Lect</char> it<char style="add">e</char> syr<char style="add">p, h</char> arm geo slav Basil Chrysostom</char></note> τῆς διακονίας ταύτης καὶ ἀποστολῆς ἀφ᾽ ἧς παρέβη Ἰούδας πορευθῆναι εἰς τὸν τόπον τὸν ἴδιον. <verse number="26" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">1.26 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="PRO 16:33">Pr 16.33</ref></char></note>καὶ ἔδωκαν κλήρους αὐτοῖς<note caller="5" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">1.26 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{B} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">αὐτοῖς </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ A B C D<char style="add">1</char> 33 81 945 1175 1409 1739 2344 <char style="it">l</char> 1178 it<char style="add">c, dem, ph, ro, w</char> vg cop<char style="add">sa, bo, meg</char> eth geo slav ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">αὐτῶν </char><char style="ft" closed="false">D* E Ψ 181 307 453 610 614 1678 <char style="it">Byz</char> <char style="it">Lect</char> it<char style="add">ar, d, e, gig, p, sa, r</char> vg<char style="add">ms</char> syr<char style="add">h</char> Basil Chrysostom; Augustine</char></note> καὶ ἔπεσεν ὁ κλῆρος ἐπὶ Μαθθίαν καὶ συγκατεψηφίσθη μετὰ τῶν ἕνδεκα ἀποστόλων.</para>
  <chapter number="2" style="c" />
  <para style="s">The Coming of the Holy Spirit</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">2.1 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">τὴν … πεντηκοστῆς </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="LEV 23:15-21">Lv 23.15‑21</ref>; <ref loc="DEU 16:9-11">Dt 16.9‑11</ref></char>
    </note>Καὶ ἐν τῷ συμπληροῦσθαι τὴν ἡμέραν τῆς πεντηκοστῆς ἦσαν πάντες ὁμοῦ ἐπὶ τὸ αὐτό. <verse number="2" style="v" />καὶ ἐγένετο ἄφνω ἐκ τοῦ οὐρανοῦ ἦχος ὥσπερ φερομένης πνοῆς βιαίας καὶ ἐπλήρωσεν ὅλον τὸν οἶκον οὗ ἦσαν καθήμενοι <verse number="3" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">2.3‑4 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ὤφθησαν … ἁγίου </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 3:11">Mt 3.11</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 3:16">Lk 3.16</ref></char></note>καὶ ὤφθησαν αὐτοῖς διαμεριζόμεναι γλῶσσαι ὡσεὶ πυρὸς καὶ ἐκάθισεν ἐφ᾽ ἕνα ἕκαστον αὐτῶν, <verse number="4" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">2.4 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ἐπλήσθησαν … ἁγίου </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 4:31">Ac 4.31</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 10:44-45">10.44‑45</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 19:6">19.6</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ἤρξαντο … γλώσσαις </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MRK 16:17">Mk 16.17</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 10:46">Ac 10.46</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 19:6">19.6</ref>; <ref loc="1CO 13:1">1 Cor 13.1</ref></char></note>καὶ ἐπλήσθησαν πάντες πνεύματος ἁγίου καὶ ἤρξαντο λαλεῖν ἑτέραις γλώσσαις καθὼς τὸ πνεῦμα ἐδίδου ἀποφθέγγεσθαι αὐτοῖς.</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="5" style="v" />Ἦσαν δὲ εἰς Ἰερουσαλὴμ κατοικοῦντες Ἰουδαῖοι, ἄνδρες εὐλαβεῖς<note caller="1" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">2.5 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{B} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">κατοικοῦντες Ἰουδαῖοι, ἄνδρες εὐλαβεῖς </char><char style="ft" closed="false">A B (C <char style="it">transpose</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">κατοικοῦντες ἐν Ἰερουσαλήμ, </char><char style="ft" closed="false"><char style="it">but</char> C* <char style="it">also</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἄνδρες Ἰουδαῖοι</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) (D </char><char style="fk" closed="false">εὐλαβεῖς ἄνδρες</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) (E </char><char style="fk" closed="false">Ἰουδαῖοι κατοικοῦντες</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) Ψ 33 81 181 307 453 610 614 945 1175 1409 1678 1739 2344 2818 <char style="it">Byz</char> <char style="it">Lect</char> it<char style="add">ar, c, (d), dem, (e), gig, p, r, ro, t, w</char> vg syr<char style="add">p, h, pal</char> cop<char style="add">sa, bo, meg</char> arm (eth) geo slav (Eusebius) Chrysostom; Hilary Jerome (Augustine) ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">κατοικοῦντες ἄνδρες εὐλαβεῖς </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ <char style="it">l</char> 884 it<char style="add">ph</char> vg<char style="add">ms</char> BJ</char></note> ἀπὸ παντὸς ἔθνους τῶν ὑπὸ τὸν οὐρανόν. <verse number="6" style="v" />γενομένης δὲ τῆς φωνῆς ταύτης συνῆλθεν τὸ πλῆθος καὶ συνεχύθη, ὅτι ἤκουον εἷς ἕκαστος τῇ ἰδίᾳ διαλέκτῳ λαλούντων αὐτῶν. <verse number="7" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">2.7 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">Οὐχ … Γαλιλαῖοι </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 1:11">Ac 1.11</ref></char></note>ἐξίσταντο δὲ καὶ ἐθαύμαζον λέγοντες, Οὐχ ἰδοὺ ἅπαντες οὗτοί εἰσιν οἱ λαλοῦντες Γαλιλαῖοι; <verse number="8" style="v" />καὶ πῶς ἡμεῖς ἀκούομεν ἕκαστος τῇ ἰδίᾳ διαλέκτῳ ἡμῶν ἐν ᾗ ἐγεννήθημεν; <verse number="9" style="v" />Πάρθοι καὶ Μῆδοι καὶ Ἐλαμῖται καὶ οἱ κατοικοῦντες τὴν Μεσοποταμίαν, Ἰουδαίαν τε καὶ Καππαδοκίαν, Πόντον καὶ τὴν Ἀσίαν, <verse number="10" style="v" />Φρυγίαν τε καὶ Παμφυλίαν, Αἴγυπτον καὶ τὰ μέρη τῆς Λιβύης τῆς κατὰ Κυρήνην, καὶ οἱ ἐπιδημοῦντες Ῥωμαῖοι, <verse number="11" style="v" />Ἰουδαῖοί τε καὶ προσήλυτοι, Κρῆτες καὶ Ἄραβες, ἀκούομεν λαλούντων αὐτῶν ταῖς ἡμετέραις γλώσσαις τὰ μεγαλεῖα τοῦ θεοῦ. <verse number="12" style="v" />ἐξίσταντο δὲ πάντες καὶ διηπόρουν, ἄλλος πρὸς ἄλλον λέγοντες, Τί θέλει τοῦτο εἶναι; <verse number="13" style="v" />ἕτεροι δὲ διαχλευάζοντες ἔλεγον ὅτι Γλεύκους μεμεστωμένοι εἰσίν.</para>
  <para style="s">Peter’s Speech at Pentecost</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="14" style="v" />Σταθεὶς δὲ ὁ Πέτρος σὺν τοῖς ἕνδεκα ἐπῆρεν τὴν φωνὴν αὐτοῦ καὶ ἀπεφθέγξατο αὐτοῖς, Ἄνδρες Ἰουδαῖοι καὶ οἱ κατοικοῦντες Ἰερουσαλὴμ πάντες, τοῦτο ὑμῖν γνωστὸν ἔστω καὶ ἐνωτίσασθε τὰ ῥήματά μου. <verse number="15" style="v" />οὐ γὰρ ὡς ὑμεῖς ὑπολαμβάνετε οὗτοι μεθύουσιν, ἔστιν γὰρ ὥρα τρίτη τῆς ἡμέρας, <verse number="16" style="v" />ἀλλὰ τοῦτό ἐστιν τὸ εἰρημένον διὰ τοῦ προφήτου Ἰωήλ<note caller="2" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">2.16 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{B} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">προφήτου Ἰωήλ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ A B C E Ψ 076<char style="add">vid</char> 096 33 81 181 307 453 610 614 945 1175 1409 1678 1739 2344 2818 <char style="it">Byz</char> [P] <char style="it">Lect</char> it<char style="add">ar, c, dem, e, (gig), p, ph, ro, t, w</char> vg syr<char style="add">p, h, pal</char> cop<char style="add">(sa), bo, (meg)</char> arm (eth) geo slav Basil Cyril-Jerusalem (Ps-Dionysius) Chrysostom Severian; Jerome (Gaudentius) ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">προφήτου </char><char style="ft" closed="false">D it<char style="add">d, r</char> Irenaeus<char style="add">lat</char>; Rebaptism Hilary Gregory-Elvira Augustine BJ</char></note>·</para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="17" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">2.17‑21 </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="JOL 2:28-32">Jl 2.28‑32</ref> (3.1‑5 <char style="sc">lxx</char>)</char>
    </note>
    <char style="qt">Καὶ ἔσται</char> ἐν ταῖς ἐσχάταις ἡμέραις, λέγει ὁ θεός,</para>
  <para style="q1">
    <char style="qt">ἐκχεῶ ἀπὸ τοῦ πνεύματός μου ἐπὶ πᾶσαν σάρκα,</char></para>
  <para style="q2">
    <char style="qt">καὶ προφητεύσουσιν οἱ υἱοὶ ὑμῶν καὶ αἱ θυγατέρες ὑμῶν</char></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <char style="qt">καὶ οἱ νεανίσκοι ὑμῶν ὁράσεις ὄψονται</char></para>
  <para style="q2">
    <char style="qt">καὶ οἱ πρεσβύτεροι ὑμῶν ἐνυπνίοις ἐνυπνιασθήσονται·</char></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="18" style="v" />
    <char style="qt">καί γε ἐπὶ τοὺς δούλους μου καὶ ἐπὶ τὰς δούλας μου</char></para>
  <para style="q2">
    <char style="qt">ἐν ταῖς ἡμέραις ἐκείναις</char>
    <note caller="3" style="f">
      <char style="fr" closed="false">2.18 </char>
      <char style="ft" closed="false">{A} </char>
      <char style="fk" closed="false">ἐν ταῖς ἡμέραις ἐκείναις </char>
      <char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">74</char> ℵ A B C E Ψ 076 33 81 181 307 453 610 614 (945 <char style="it">after</char> </char>
      <char style="fk" closed="false">πνεύματός μου</char>
      <char style="ft" closed="false">) 1175 1409 1678 1739 1891 2344 2818 <char style="it">Byz</char> [P] <char style="it">Lect</char> (<char style="it">l</char> 165 <char style="it">l</char> 1021 </char>
      <char style="fk" closed="false">ἡμέραις ταύταις</char>
      <char style="ft" closed="false">) it<char style="add">ar, c, dem, e, p, ph, ro<char style="add">2</char>, t, w</char> vg syr<char style="add">p, h, pal</char> cop<char style="add">sa, bo<char style="add">(mss)</char>, meg</char> arm (eth) geo slav Cyril-Jerusalem Chrysostom ⫽ <char style="it">omit</char> D it<char style="add">d, gig, r, ro*</char> vg<char style="add">ms</char> Asterius Didymus; Rebaptism Priscillian Jerome BJ</char>
    </note> <char style="qt">ἐκχεῶ ἀπὸ τοῦ πνεύματός μου,</char></para>
  <para style="q3">καὶ προφητεύσουσιν<note caller="4" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">2.18 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{A} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">καὶ προφητεύσουσιν </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">74</char> ℵ A B C E Ψ 076<char style="add">vid</char> 33 81 181 307 453 610 614 945 1175 1409 1678 1739 1891 2344 2818 <char style="it">Byz</char> [P] <char style="it">Lect</char> (<char style="it">l</char> 680 </char><char style="fk" closed="false">προφητεύσωσιν</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) it<char style="add">ar, c, dem, e, gig, ph, r, ro, t, w</char> vg syr<char style="add">p, h, pal</char> cop<char style="add">sa, bo, meg</char> arm eth geo slav Asterius Cyril-Jerusalem Didymus Chrysostom ⫽ <char style="it">omit</char> (see <char style="xt"><ref loc="JOL 2:29">Jl 2.29</ref>)</char> D it<char style="add">d, p</char> Rebaptism Priscillian Jerome BJ</char></note>.</para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="19" style="v" />
    <char style="qt">καὶ δώσω τέρατα ἐν τῷ οὐρανῷ</char> ἄνω</para>
  <para style="q2">
    <char style="qt">καὶ</char> σημεῖα <char style="qt">ἐπὶ τῆς γῆς</char> κάτω,</para>
  <para style="q3">
    <char style="qt">αἷμα καὶ πῦρ καὶ ἀτμίδα καπνοῦ</char>
    <note caller="5" style="f">
      <char style="fr" closed="false">2.19 </char>
      <char style="ft" closed="false">{A} </char>
      <char style="fk" closed="false">αἷμα καὶ πῦρ καὶ ἀτμίδα καπνοῦ </char>
      <char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">74vid</char> ℵ A B C E Ψ 076 33 81 181 307 453 610 614 945 1175 1409 1678 1739 1891 2344 2818 <char style="it">Byz</char> [P] <char style="it">Lect</char> it<char style="add">ar, c, dem, e, ph, ro, t, w</char> vg syr<char style="add">p, h, pal</char> cop<char style="add">sa, bo, meg</char> arm eth geo slav Didymus Chrysostom Severian ⫽ <char style="it">omit</char> D it<char style="add">d, gig, p, r</char> Priscillian BJ</char>
    </note>·</para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="20" style="v" />
    <char style="qt">ὁ ἥλιος μεταστραφήσεται εἰς σκότος</char></para>
  <para style="q2">
    <char style="qt">καὶ ἡ σελήνη εἰς αἷμα,</char></para>
  <para style="q3">
    <char style="qt">πρὶν ἐλθεῖν ἡμέραν κυρίου τὴν μεγάλην καὶ ἐπιφανῆ.</char></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="21" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">2.21 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">πᾶς … σωθήσεται </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="ROM 10:13">Ro 10.13</ref>
      </char>
    </note>
    <char style="qt">καὶ ἔσται πᾶς ὃς ἂν ἐπικαλέσηται τὸ ὄνομα κυρίου σωθήσεται.</char></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="22" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">2.22 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">Ἰησοῦν … ὑμῶν </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="JHN 3:2">Jn 3.2</ref>
      </char>
    </note>Ἄνδρες Ἰσραηλῖται, ἀκούσατε τοὺς λόγους τούτους· Ἰησοῦν τὸν Ναζωραῖον, ἄνδρα ἀποδεδειγμένον ἀπὸ τοῦ θεοῦ εἰς ὑμᾶς δυνάμεσιν καὶ τέρασιν καὶ σημείοις οἷς ἐποίησεν δι᾽ αὐτοῦ ὁ θεὸς ἐν μέσῳ ὑμῶν καθὼς αὐτοὶ οἴδατε, <verse number="23" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">2.23 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">τοῦτον … ἔκδοτον </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 4:28">Ac 4.28</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">διὰ … ἀνείλατε </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 27:35">Mt 27.35</ref>, <ref loc="MAT 27:50">50</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 15:24">Mk 15.24</ref>, <ref loc="MRK 15:37">37</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 23:33">Lk 23.33</ref>, <ref loc="LUK 23:46">46</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 19:18">Jn 19.18</ref>, <ref loc="JHN 19:30">30</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 3:15">Ac 3.15</ref></char></note>τοῦτον τῇ ὡρισμένῃ βουλῇ καὶ προγνώσει τοῦ θεοῦ ἔκδοτον διὰ χειρὸς ἀνόμων προσπήξαντες ἀνείλατε, <verse number="24" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">2.24 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ὃν … ἀνέστησεν </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 28:6">Mt 28.6</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 16:6">Mk 16.6</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 24:5">Lk 24.5</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 3:15">Ac 3.15</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ὠδῖνας τοῦ θανάτου </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="2SA 22:6">2 Sm 22.6</ref>; <ref loc="PSA 18:4">Ps 18.4</ref>; <ref loc="PSA 116:3">116.3</ref></char></note>ὃν ὁ θεὸς ἀνέστησεν λύσας τὰς ὠδῖνας τοῦ θανάτου<note caller="6" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">2.24 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{A} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">θανάτου </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">74vid</char> ℵ A B C E Ψ 095<char style="add">vid</char> 33 81 181 307 453 610 614 945 1175 1409 1678 1739 1891 2344 2818 <char style="it">Byz</char> [P] <char style="it">Lect</char> (<char style="it">l</char> 1441 </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τοῦ θανάτου τὰς ὠδῖνας</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) syr<char style="add">h, pal</char> cop<char style="add">sa</char> arm eth geo slav Eusebius Athanasius Ps-Athanasius Gregory-Nyssa Chrysostom Cyril Theodotus-Ancyra; Greek mss<char style="add">acc. to Bede</char> ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ᾅδου </char><char style="ft" closed="false">(see <char style="xt"><ref loc="ACT 2:27">2.27</ref>, <ref loc="ACT 2:31">31</ref>)</char> D it<char style="add">ar, c, d, dem, e, gig, p, ph, r, ro, t, w</char> vg syr<char style="add">p</char> cop<char style="add">bo, meg</char> Polycarp Irenaeus<char style="add">lat</char> Epiphanius; Augustine BJ</char></note>, καθότι οὐκ ἦν δυνατὸν κρατεῖσθαι αὐτὸν ὑπ᾽ αὐτοῦ. <verse number="25" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">2.25‑28 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">Προορώμην … σου </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="PSA 16:8-11">Ps 16.8‑11</ref></char></note>Δαυὶδ γὰρ λέγει εἰς αὐτόν,</para>
  <para style="q1">
    <char style="qt">Προορώμην τὸν κύριον ἐνώπιόν μου διὰ παντός,</char></para>
  <para style="q2">
    <char style="qt">ὅτι ἐκ δεξιῶν μού ἐστιν ἵνα μὴ σαλευθῶ.</char></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="26" style="v" />
    <char style="qt">διὰ τοῦτο ηὐφράνθη ἡ καρδία μου καὶ ἠγαλλιάσατο ἡ γλῶσσά μου,</char></para>
  <para style="q2">
    <char style="qt">ἔτι δὲ καὶ ἡ σάρξ μου κατασκηνώσει ἐπ᾽ ἐλπίδι,</char></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="27" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">2.27 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">οὐδὲ … διαφθοράν </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="ACT 13:35">Ac 13.35</ref>
      </char>
    </note>
    <char style="qt">ὅτι οὐκ ἐγκαταλείψεις τὴν ψυχήν μου εἰς ᾅδην</char></para>
  <para style="q2">
    <char style="qt">οὐδὲ δώσεις τὸν ὅσιόν σου ἰδεῖν διαφθοράν.</char></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="28" style="v" />
    <char style="qt">ἐγνώρισάς μοι ὁδοὺς ζωῆς,</char></para>
  <para style="q2">
    <char style="qt">πληρώσεις με εὐφροσύνης μετὰ τοῦ προσώπου σου.</char></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="29" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">2.29 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">περὶ … ἐτάφη </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="1KI 2:10">1 Kgs 2.10</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 13:36">Ac 13.36</ref></char>
    </note>Ἄνδρες ἀδελφοί, ἐξὸν εἰπεῖν μετὰ παρρησίας πρὸς ὑμᾶς περὶ τοῦ πατριάρχου Δαυὶδ ὅτι καὶ ἐτελεύτησεν καὶ ἐτάφη, καὶ τὸ μνῆμα αὐτοῦ ἔστιν ἐν ἡμῖν ἄχρι τῆς ἡμέρας ταύτης. <verse number="30" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">2.30 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ὤμοσεν … θρόνον αὐτοῦ </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="PSA 132:11">Ps 132.11</ref>; <ref loc="2SA 7:12-13">2 Sm 7.12‑13</ref></char></note>προφήτης οὖν ὑπάρχων, καὶ εἰδὼς ὅτι ὅρκῳ <char style="qt">ὤμοσεν αὐτῷ</char> ὁ θεὸς <char style="qt">ἐκ καρποῦ τῆς ὀσφύος αὐτοῦ καθίσαι</char><note caller="7" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">2.30 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{B} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">καθίσαι </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ A B C (D<char style="add">1</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">καὶ καθίσαι</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) 81 1175 it<char style="add">ar, c, dem, gig, p, ph, r, ro, t, w</char> vg syr<char style="add">p, pal</char> cop<char style="add">sa, bo</char> arm eth Irenaeus<char style="add">lat</char> Eusebius Cyril; Victorinus-Rome Jerome ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τὸ κατὰ σάρκα ἀναστήσειν τὸν Χριστὸν καθίσαι </char><char style="ft" closed="false">(Ψ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">καὶ καθίσαι</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) (33 181 </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἀναστῆσαι</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) 614 945 1409 2344 <char style="it">Byz</char> [P] <char style="it">Lect</char> (<char style="it">l</char> 938 <char style="it">l</char> 1364 </char><char style="fk" closed="false">Ἰησοῦν </char><char style="ft" closed="false"><char style="it">for</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">Χριστόν, </char><char style="ft" closed="false"><char style="it">l</char> 156 <char style="it">l</char> 1178 </char><char style="fk" closed="false">καθήσεται</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) it<char style="add">d</char> syr<char style="add">h</char> Origen Chrysostom (Theodoret<char style="add">6/7</char>) ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">κατὰ σάρκα ἀναστῆσαι τὸν Χριστὸν καθίσαι τε </char><char style="ft" closed="false">(D* </char><char style="fk" closed="false">καὶ καθίσαι</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) 307 453 610 1678 2818 cop<char style="add">meg</char> slav ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἀναστῆσαι τὸν Χριστὸν καὶ καθίσαι </char><char style="ft" closed="false">E it<char style="add">e</char> geo Theodoret<char style="add">1/7</char>; Greek ms<char style="add">acc. to Bede</char> ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἀναστήσειν τὸν Χριστὸν καθίσαι </char><char style="ft" closed="false">1739 1891</char></note> <char style="qt">ἐπὶ τὸν θρόνον αὐτοῦ</char>, <verse number="31" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">2.31 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">οὔτε ἐγκατελείφθη … διαφθοράν </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="PSA 16:10">Ps 16.10</ref></char></note>προϊδὼν ἐλάλησεν περὶ τῆς ἀναστάσεως τοῦ Χριστοῦ ὅτι</para>
  <para style="q1">
    <char style="qt">οὔτε ἐγκατελείφθη εἰς ᾅδην</char></para>
  <para style="q2">
    <char style="qt">οὔτε</char> ἡ σὰρξ αὐτοῦ <char style="qt">εἶδεν διαφθοράν.</char></para>
  <para style="m">
    <verse number="32" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">2.32 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">οὗ … μάρτυρες </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="LUK 24:48">Lk 24.48</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 1:8">Ac 1.8</ref></char>
    </note>τοῦτον τὸν Ἰησοῦν ἀνέστησεν ὁ θεός, οὗ πάντες ἡμεῖς ἐσμεν μάρτυρες· <verse number="33" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">2.33 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">τῇ … ὑψωθείς </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MRK 16:19">Mk 16.19</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 7:55">Ac 7.55</ref>, <ref loc="ACT 7:56">56</ref>; <ref loc="ROM 8:34">Ro 8.34</ref>; <ref loc="COL 3:1">Col 3.1</ref>; <ref loc="HEB 1:3">He 1.3</ref>; <ref loc="HEB 8:1">8.1</ref>; <ref loc="HEB 10:12">10.12</ref>; <ref loc="HEB 12:2">12.2</ref>; <ref loc="1PE 3:22">1 Pe 3.22</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">τήν … πατρός </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="JHN 14:16-17">Jn 14.16‑17</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 15:26">15.26</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 1:4">Ac 1.4</ref></char></note>τῇ δεξιᾷ οὖν τοῦ θεοῦ ὑψωθείς, τήν τε ἐπαγγελίαν τοῦ πνεύματος τοῦ ἁγίου λαβὼν παρὰ τοῦ πατρός, ἐξέχεεν τοῦτο ὃ ὑμεῖς [καὶ] βλέπετε καὶ ἀκούετε. <verse number="34" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">2.34‑35 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">Εἶπεν … ποδῶν σου </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="PSA 110:1">Ps 110.1</ref> (<ref loc="MAT 22:44">Mt 22.44</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 12:36">Mk 12.36</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 20:42-43">Lk 20.42‑43</ref>; <ref loc="HEB 1:13">He 1.13</ref>)</char></note>οὐ γὰρ Δαυὶδ ἀνέβη εἰς τοὺς οὐρανούς, λέγει δὲ αὐτός,</para>
  <para style="q1">
    <char style="qt">Εἶπεν [ὁ] κύριος τῷ κυρίῳ μου,</char></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <char style="qt">Κάθου ἐκ δεξιῶν μου,</char></para>
  <para style="q2">
    <verse number="35" style="v" />
    <char style="qt">ἕως ἂν θῶ τοὺς ἐχθρούς σου ὑποπόδιον τῶν ποδῶν σου.</char></para>
  <para style="m">
    <verse number="36" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">2.36 </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="ACT 5:30-31">Ac 5.30‑31</ref>
      </char>
    </note>ἀσφαλῶς οὖν γινωσκέτω πᾶς οἶκος Ἰσραὴλ ὅτι καὶ κύριον αὐτὸν καὶ Χριστὸν ἐποίησεν ὁ θεός, τοῦτον τὸν Ἰησοῦν ὃν ὑμεῖς ἐσταυρώσατε.</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="37" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">2.37 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">Τί ποιήσωμεν </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="LUK 3:10">Lk 3.10</ref>, <ref loc="LUK 3:12">12</ref>, <ref loc="LUK 3:14">14</ref></char>
    </note>Ἀκούσαντες δὲ κατενύγησαν τὴν καρδίαν εἶπόν τε πρὸς τὸν Πέτρον καὶ τοὺς λοιποὺς<note caller="8" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">2.37 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{A} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">λοιπούς </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">74vid</char> ℵ A B C E Ψ 33 81 181 307 453 610 614 945 1175 1409 1678 1739 1891 2344 2818 <char style="it">Byz</char> [P] <char style="it">l</char> 1178 <char style="it">l</char><char style="add">AD</char> it<char style="add">ar, c, dem, e, p, ph, ro, t, w</char> vg syr<char style="add">p, h</char> cop<char style="add">sa, bo, meg</char> arm geo slav Hippolytus Basil Chrysostom<char style="add">lem</char> ⫽ <char style="it">omit</char> D it<char style="add">d, gig, r</char> cop<char style="add">bo<char style="add">mss</char></char> Hippolytus<char style="add">arm</char>; Augustine</char></note> ἀποστόλους, Τί ποιήσωμεν, ἄνδρες ἀδελφοί; <verse number="38" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">2.38 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">Μετανοήσατε … ἁμαρτιῶν ὑμῶν </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 3:19">Ac 3.19</ref></char></note>Πέτρος δὲ πρὸς αὐτούς, Μετανοήσατε, [φησίν,] καὶ βαπτισθήτω ἕκαστος ὑμῶν ἐπὶ τῷ ὀνόματι Ἰησοῦ Χριστοῦ εἰς ἄφεσιν τῶν ἁμαρτιῶν ὑμῶν καὶ λήμψεσθε τὴν δωρεὰν<note caller="a" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">2.38 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">C: GNB BTI (DHH)</char></note> τοῦ ἁγίου πνεύματος. <verse number="39" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">2.39 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">τοῖς εἰς μακράν </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ISA 57:19">Is 57.19</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ὅσους … κύριος </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="JOL 2:32">Jl 2.32</ref>; <ref loc="ROM 10:13">Ro 10.13</ref></char></note>ὑμῖν γάρ ἐστιν ἡ ἐπαγγελία καὶ τοῖς τέκνοις ὑμῶν καὶ πᾶσιν τοῖς εἰς μακράν, ὅσους ἂν προσκαλέσηται κύριος ὁ θεὸς ἡμῶν. <verse number="40" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">2.40 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">τῆς γενεᾶς … ταύτης </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="DEU 32:5">Dt 32.5</ref>; <ref loc="PSA 78:8">Ps 78.8</ref>; <ref loc="PHP 2:15">Php 2.15</ref></char></note>ἑτέροις τε λόγοις πλείοσιν διεμαρτύρατο καὶ παρεκάλει αὐτοὺς λέγων, Σώθητε ἀπὸ τῆς γενεᾶς τῆς σκολιᾶς ταύτης. <verse number="41" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">2.41 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 2:47">Ac 2.47</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 4:4">4.4</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 5:14">5.14</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 6:7">6.7</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 11:21">11.21</ref>, <ref loc="ACT 11:24">24</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 21:20">21.20</ref></char></note>οἱ μὲν οὖν ἀποδεξάμενοι τὸν λόγον αὐτοῦ ἐβαπτίσθησαν καὶ προσετέθησαν ἐν τῇ ἡμέρᾳ ἐκείνῃ ψυχαὶ ὡσεὶ τρισχίλιαι. <verse number="42" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">2.42 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">τῇ κλάσει τοῦ ἄρτου </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 2:46">Ac 2.46</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 20:7">20.7</ref></char></note>ἦσαν δὲ προσκαρτεροῦντες τῇ διδαχῇ τῶν ἀποστόλων καὶ τῇ κοινωνίᾳ, τῇ κλάσει τοῦ ἄρτου καὶ ταῖς προσευχαῖς.</para>
  <para style="s">Life among the Believers</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="43" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">2.43 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">Ἐγίνετο … φόβος </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="ACT 5:5">Ac 5.5</ref>, <ref loc="ACT 5:11">11</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 19:17">19.17</ref> </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">πολλά … ἐγίνετο </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="ACT 5:12">Ac 5.12</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 6:8">6.8</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 14:3">14.3</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 15:12">15.12</ref></char>
    </note>Ἐγίνετο δὲ πάσῃ ψυχῇ φόβος, πολλά τε τέρατα καὶ σημεῖα διὰ τῶν ἀποστόλων ἐγίνετο<note caller="9" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">2.43 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{C} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">διὰ τῶν ἀποστόλων ἐγίνετο </char><char style="ft" closed="false">B D 81 945 1739 1891 <char style="it">Byz</char> [P] <char style="it">Lect</char><char style="add">pt, AD</char> (<char style="it">Lect</char><char style="add">pt</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἐγένετο</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) it<char style="add">d, gig, p*, r</char> syr<char style="add">h</char> cop<char style="add">sa</char> (arm) (eth) Chrysostom ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">διὰ τῶν ἀποστόλων ἐγίνετο ἐν Ἰερουσαλήμ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">33 1409 (2344 </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἐγένετο</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) syr<char style="add">p</char> ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">διὰ τῶν ἀποστόλων ἐγίνετο ἐν Ἰερουσαλήμ· φόβος τε ἦν μέγας ἐπὶ πάντας </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">74vid</char> ℵ (A C </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἐγένετο διὰ τῶν ἀποστόλων</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) </char><char style="fk" closed="false">(2818 </char><char style="fk" closed="false">εἰς Ἰερουσαλήμ </char><char style="ft" closed="false"><char style="it">and</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">πάντας αὐτούς</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) (1175 </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἐγίνετο διὰ τῶν ἀποστόλων</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) (<char style="it">l</char> 884 </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἐγένετο</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) it<char style="add">ar, c, dem, p<char style="add">2</char>, ph, ro, t, w</char> vg<char style="add">ww, st</char> (vg<char style="add">cl</char>) (slav) ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">διὰ τῶν χειρῶν τῶν ἀποστόλων ἐγίνετο ἐν Ἰερουσαλήμ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">(E </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἐγίνοντο</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) 181* (181<char style="add">c</char> <char style="it">add</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">φόβος τε ἦν ἐπὶ πάντας</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) (614 <char style="it">omit</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἐν Ἰερουσαλήμ</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) it<char style="add">e</char> ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">διὰ τῶν χειρῶν τῶν ἀποστόλων ἐγίνοντο εἰς Ἰερουσαλήμ· φόβος τε ἦν μέγας ἐπὶ πάντας αὐτούς </char><char style="ft" closed="false">(Ψ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἐν </char><char style="ft" closed="false"><char style="it">for</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">εἰς</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) 307 453 610 1678 (cop<char style="add">bo, meg</char>) (geo)</char></note>. <verse number="44" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">2.44 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 4:32">Ac 4.32</ref></char></note>πάντες δὲ οἱ πιστεύοντες ἦσαν ἐπὶ τὸ αὐτὸ καὶ<note caller="10" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">2.44 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{A} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἦσαν ἐπὶ τὸ αὐτὸ καί </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">74</char> ℵ A C D E Ψ 33 81 181 307 453 610 614 945 1175 1409 1678 1739 1891 2344 2818 <char style="it">Byz</char> [P] <char style="it">l</char> 884 <char style="it">l</char> 1178 it<char style="add">ar, c, d, dem, e, ph, ro, t, w</char> vg syr<char style="add">h</char> arm eth geo slav Basil Chrysostom ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἐπὶ τὸ αὐτό </char><char style="ft" closed="false">B it<char style="add">p, r</char> Origen; Speculum Salvian REB BJ ⫽ <char style="it">omit</char> it<char style="add">gig</char></char></note> εἶχον ἅπαντα κοινὰ <verse number="45" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">2.45 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 4:34-35">Ac 4.34‑35</ref></char></note>καὶ τὰ κτήματα καὶ τὰς ὑπάρξεις ἐπίπρασκον καὶ διεμέριζον αὐτὰ πᾶσιν καθότι ἄν τις χρείαν εἶχεν· <verse number="46" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">2.46 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">καθ᾽ … ἱερῷ </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 24:53">Lk 24.53</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">κλῶντες … ἄρτον </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 2:42">Ac 2.42</ref></char></note>καθ᾽ ἡμέραν τε προσκαρτεροῦντες ὁμοθυμαδὸν ἐν τῷ ἱερῷ, κλῶντές τε κατ᾽ οἶκον ἄρτον, μετελάμβανον τροφῆς ἐν ἀγαλλιάσει καὶ ἀφελότητι καρδίας <verse number="47" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">2.47 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ὁ … προσετίθει … αὐτό </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 2:41">Ac 2.41</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 4:4">4.4</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 5:14">5.14</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 6:7">6.7</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 11:21">11.21</ref>, <ref loc="ACT 11:24">24</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 21:20">21.20</ref></char></note>αἰνοῦντες τὸν θεὸν καὶ ἔχοντες χάριν πρὸς ὅλον τὸν λαόν. ὁ δὲ κύριος προσετίθει τοὺς σῳζομένους καθ᾽ ἡμέραν ἐπὶ τὸ αὐτό.</para>
  <chapter number="3" style="c" />
  <para style="s">The Lame Man Healed at the Gate of the Temple</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">3.1 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">ἐπὶ … προσευχῆς τὴν ἐνάτην </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="ACT 10:3">Ac 10.3</ref>, <ref loc="ACT 10:9">9</ref>, <ref loc="ACT 10:30">30</ref></char>
    </note>Πέτρος δὲ<note caller="1" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">2.47–3.1 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{B} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἐπὶ τὸ αὐτό. Πέτρος δέ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">74vid. 91vid</char> ℵ A B C 095 81 1175 it<char style="add">ar, c, dem, gig, ph, ro, w</char> vg cop<char style="add">sa, bo</char> arm eth ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τῇ ἐκκλησίᾳ. Πέτρος δέ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">1409 geo ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τῇ ἐκκλησίᾳ. Ἐπὶ τὸ αὐτὸ δὲ Πέτρος </char><char style="ft" closed="false">E Ψ 33 (181 </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἐν τῇ ἐκκλησίᾳ</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) 453 610 614 1678 2344 (* <char style="it">omit</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">δέ</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) <char style="it">Byz</char> [P] (<char style="it">l</char> 884 <char style="it">l</char> 1178 <char style="it">finish lesson with</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἐκκλησίᾳ</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) it<char style="add">e</char> syr<char style="add">p, h</char> slav Chrysostom; Greek ms<char style="add">acc. to Bede</char> ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τῇ ἐκκλησίᾳ ἐπὶ τὸ αὐτό. Πέτρος δέ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">307 945 1739 1891 ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἐπὶ τὸ αὐτὸ ἐν τῇ ἐκκλησίᾳ. Ἐν δὲ ταῖς ἡμέραις ταύταις Πέτρος </char><char style="ft" closed="false">D it<char style="add">d</char> (it<char style="add">p, r</char> vg<char style="add">ms</char> <char style="it">omit</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τῇ ἐκκλησίᾳ</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) (cop<char style="add">meg</char>)</char></note> καὶ Ἰωάννης ἀνέβαινον εἰς τὸ ἱερὸν ἐπὶ τὴν ὥραν τῆς προσευχῆς τὴν ἐνάτην. <verse number="2" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">3.2 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">χωλὸς … αὐτοῦ </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="JHN 9:1">Jn 9.1</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 14:8">Ac 14.8</ref></char></note>καί τις ἀνὴρ χωλὸς ἐκ κοιλίας μητρὸς αὐτοῦ ὑπάρχων ἐβαστάζετο, ὃν ἐτίθουν καθ᾽ ἡμέραν πρὸς τὴν θύραν τοῦ ἱεροῦ τὴν λεγομένην Ὡραίαν τοῦ αἰτεῖν ἐλεημοσύνην παρὰ τῶν εἰσπορευομένων εἰς τὸ ἱερόν· <verse number="3" style="v" />ὃς ἰδὼν Πέτρον καὶ Ἰωάννην μέλλοντας εἰσιέναι εἰς τὸ ἱερόν, ἠρώτα ἐλεημοσύνην λαβεῖν. <verse number="4" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">3.4 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ἀτενίσας … αὐτόν </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 6:15">Ac 6.15</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 13:9">13.9</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 14:9">14.9</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 23:1">23.1</ref></char></note>ἀτενίσας δὲ Πέτρος εἰς αὐτὸν σὺν τῷ Ἰωάννῃ εἶπεν, Βλέψον εἰς ἡμᾶς. <verse number="5" style="v" />ὁ δὲ ἐπεῖχεν αὐτοῖς προσδοκῶν τι παρ᾽ αὐτῶν λαβεῖν. <verse number="6" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">3.6 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ἐν … περιπάτει </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 3:16">Ac 3.16</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 4:10">4.10</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 16:18">16.18</ref></char></note>εἶπεν δὲ Πέτρος, Ἀργύριον καὶ χρυσίον οὐχ ὑπάρχει μοι, ὃ δὲ ἔχω τοῦτό σοι δίδωμι· ἐν τῷ ὀνόματι Ἰησοῦ Χριστοῦ τοῦ Ναζωραίου [ἔγειρε καὶ] περιπάτει<note caller="2" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">3.6 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{C} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἔγειρε καὶ περιπάτει </char><char style="ft" closed="false">A C E Ψ 095 33 81 181 307 453 610 614 945 1175 1409 1678 1739 1891 2344 2818 <char style="it">Byz</char> [P] <char style="it">Lect</char> it<char style="add">ar, c, dem, e, gig, h, p(*), r, ro, w</char> vg syr<char style="add">p, h</char> cop<char style="add">bo, meg</char> arm eth geo slav Irenaeus<char style="add">lat</char> Origen<char style="add">lat</char> Eusebius Basil Chrysostom Theodoret; Cyprian Lucifer Hilary Priscillian Ambrose Jerome Chromatius Maximus ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">περιπάτει </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ B D it<char style="add">d</char> cop<char style="add">sa</char> NIV EU BJ TOB</char></note>. <verse number="7" style="v" />καὶ πιάσας αὐτὸν τῆς δεξιᾶς χειρὸς ἤγειρεν αὐτόν· παραχρῆμα δὲ ἐστερεώθησαν αἱ βάσεις αὐτοῦ καὶ τὰ σφυδρά, <verse number="8" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">3.8 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ἐξαλλόμενος … περιεπάτει </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 14:10">Ac 14.10</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">εἰσῆλθεν … ἱερόν </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="JHN 5:14">Jn 5.14</ref></char></note>καὶ ἐξαλλόμενος ἔστη καὶ περιεπάτει καὶ εἰσῆλθεν σὺν αὐτοῖς εἰς τὸ ἱερὸν περιπατῶν καὶ ἁλλόμενος καὶ αἰνῶν τὸν θεόν. <verse number="9" style="v" />καὶ εἶδεν πᾶς ὁ λαὸς αὐτὸν περιπατοῦντα καὶ αἰνοῦντα τὸν θεόν· <verse number="10" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">3.10 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ἐπεγίνωσκον … καθήμενος </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="JHN 9:8">Jn 9.8</ref></char></note>ἐπεγίνωσκον δὲ αὐτὸν ὅτι αὐτὸς ἦν ὁ πρὸς τὴν ἐλεημοσύνην καθήμενος ἐπὶ τῇ Ὡραίᾳ Πύλῃ τοῦ ἱεροῦ καὶ ἐπλήσθησαν θάμβους καὶ ἐκστάσεως ἐπὶ τῷ συμβεβηκότι αὐτῷ.</para>
  <para style="s">Peter’s Speech in Solomon’s Portico</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="11" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">3.11 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">ἐπὶ … Σολομῶντος </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="JHN 10:23">Jn 10.23</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 5:12">Ac 5.12</ref></char>
    </note>Κρατοῦντος δὲ αὐτοῦ τὸν Πέτρον καὶ τὸν Ἰωάννην συνέδραμεν πᾶς ὁ λαὸς πρὸς αὐτοὺς ἐπὶ τῇ στοᾷ τῇ καλουμένῃ Σολομῶντος ἔκθαμβοι. <verse number="12" style="v" />ἰδὼν δὲ ὁ Πέτρος ἀπεκρίνατο πρὸς τὸν λαόν, Ἄνδρες Ἰσραηλῖται, τί θαυμάζετε ἐπὶ τούτῳ ἢ ἡμῖν τί ἀτενίζετε ὡς ἰδίᾳ δυνάμει ἢ εὐσεβείᾳ πεποιηκόσιν τοῦ περιπατεῖν αὐτόν; <verse number="13" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">3.13 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ὁ θεὸς Ἀβραὰμ … ἡμῶν </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="EXO 3:6">Ex 3.6</ref>, <ref loc="EXO 3:15">15</ref>; <ref loc="MAT 22:32">Mt 22.32</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 12:26">Mk 12.26</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 7:32">Ac 7.32</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ἐδόξασεν … Ἰησοῦν </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ISA 52:13">Is 52.13</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 13:32">Jn 13.32</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ὃν … ἀπολύειν </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 23:14-23">Lk 23.14‑23</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 18:38-40">Jn 18.38‑40</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 19:12-15">19.12‑15</ref></char></note><char style="qt">ὁ θεὸς Ἀβραὰμ καὶ [ὁ θεὸς] Ἰσαὰκ καὶ [ὁ θεὸς] Ἰακώβ, ὁ θεὸς τῶν πατέρων ἡμῶν,</char> ἐδόξασεν τὸν παῖδα αὐτοῦ Ἰησοῦν ὃν ὑμεῖς μὲν παρεδώκατε καὶ ἠρνήσασθε κατὰ πρόσωπον Πιλάτου, κρίναντος ἐκείνου ἀπολύειν· <verse number="14" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">3.14 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 27:20-21">Mt 27.20‑21</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 15:7">Mk 15.7</ref>, <ref loc="MRK 15:11-12">11‑12</ref></char></note>ὑμεῖς δὲ τὸν ἅγιον καὶ δίκαιον ἠρνήσασθε<note caller="3" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">3.14 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{A} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἠρνήσασθε </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">74</char> ℵ A B C E Ψ 33 81 181 307 453 610 614 945 1175 1409 1678 1739 1891 2344 2818 <char style="it">Byz</char> [P] <char style="it">Lect</char> it<char style="add">ar, c, dem, e, gig, h, p, ph, ro, w</char> vg syr<char style="add">p, h</char> cop<char style="add">sa, bo, meg</char> arm eth geo slav Didymus Didymus<char style="add">dub</char> Chrysostom Cyril Theodotus-Ancyra; Jerome Quodvultdeus ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἐβαρύνατε </char><char style="ft" closed="false">D it<char style="add">d</char> Irenaeus<char style="add">lat</char></char></note> καὶ ᾐτήσασθε ἄνδρα φονέα χαρισθῆναι ὑμῖν, <verse number="15" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">3.15 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">τὸν … νεκρῶν </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 4:10">Ac 4.10</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 5:30">5.30</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">οὗ ἡμεῖς μάρτυρές ἐσμεν </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 24:48">Lk 24.48</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 1:8">Ac 1.8</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 2:32">2.32</ref></char></note>τὸν δὲ ἀρχηγὸν τῆς ζωῆς ἀπεκτείνατε ὃν ὁ θεὸς ἤγειρεν ἐκ νεκρῶν, οὗ ἡμεῖς μάρτυρές ἐσμεν. <verse number="16" style="v" />καὶ ἐπὶ τῇ πίστει τοῦ ὀνόματος αὐτοῦ τοῦτον ὃν θεωρεῖτε καὶ οἴδατε, ἐστερέωσεν τὸ ὄνομα αὐτοῦ, καὶ ἡ πίστις ἡ δι᾽ αὐτοῦ ἔδωκεν αὐτῷ τὴν ὁλοκληρίαν ταύτην ἀπέναντι πάντων ὑμῶν. <verse number="17" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">3.17 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 23:34">Lk 23.34</ref>; <ref loc="1TI 1:13">1 Tm 1.13</ref></char></note>καὶ νῦν, ἀδελφοί, οἶδα ὅτι κατὰ ἄγνοιαν ἐπράξατε ὥσπερ καὶ οἱ ἄρχοντες ὑμῶν· <verse number="18" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">3.18 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 24:27">Lk 24.27</ref>, <ref loc="LUK 24:44">44</ref>, <ref loc="LUK 24:46">46</ref></char></note>ὁ δὲ θεός, ἃ προκατήγγειλεν διὰ στόματος πάντων τῶν προφητῶν παθεῖν τὸν χριστὸν αὐτοῦ, ἐπλήρωσεν οὕτως. <verse number="19" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">3.19 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 2:38">Ac 2.38</ref></char></note>μετανοήσατε οὖν καὶ ἐπιστρέψατε εἰς τὸ ἐξαλειφθῆναι ὑμῶν τὰς ἁμαρτίας, <verse number="20" style="v" />ὅπως ἂν ἔλθωσιν καιροὶ ἀναψύξεως ἀπὸ προσώπου τοῦ κυρίου καὶ ἀποστείλῃ τὸν προκεχειρισμένον ὑμῖν Χριστὸν Ἰησοῦν, <verse number="21" style="v" />ὃν δεῖ οὐρανὸν μὲν δέξασθαι ἄχρι χρόνων ἀποκαταστάσεως πάντων ὧν ἐλάλησεν ὁ θεὸς διὰ στόματος τῶν ἁγίων ἀπ᾽ αἰῶνος αὐτοῦ προφητῶν<note caller="4" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">3.21 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{B} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἀπ᾽ αἰῶνος αὐτοῦ προφητῶν </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">74</char> ℵ* A B* C 81 307 453 1175 1739 (1891* </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἁγίων αὐτοῦ προφητῶν</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) it<char style="add">e</char> ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τῶν ἀπ᾽ αἰῶνος αὐτοῦ προφητῶν </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ<char style="add">2</char> B<char style="add">2</char> E 610 945 1409 1678 2818 (<char style="it">l</char> 60 </char><char style="fk" closed="false">προφητῶν αὐτοῦ</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">αὐτοῦ προφητῶν ἀπ᾽ αἰῶνος </char><char style="ft" closed="false">(Ψ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τῶν ἀπ᾽ αἰῶνος</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) (33<char style="add">vid</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τῶν ἀπ᾽ αἰῶνος προφητῶν</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) 181 (614 </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τῶν προφητῶν ἁγίων αὐτοῦ</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) 1891<char style="add">c</char> <char style="it">Byz</char> [P] <char style="it">Lect</char> (<char style="it">l</char> 165 </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τῶν ἀπ᾽ αἰῶνος</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) (it<char style="add">ar, dem, c, ph, ro, w</char> vg) (syr<char style="add">p, h</char>) (eth) (slav) Origen<char style="add">(gr), lat1/3</char> (Chrysostom) ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τῶν προφητῶν </char><char style="ft" closed="false">D* (D<char style="add">c</char> BJ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">αὐτοῦ προφητῶν</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) it<char style="add">d, gig, h, p</char> arm geo Irenaeus<char style="add">lat</char> Origen<char style="add">lat2/3</char>; Tertullian</char></note>. <verse number="22" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">3.22 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="DEU 18:15-16">Dt 18.15‑16</ref> (<ref loc="ACT 7:37">Ac 7.37</ref>)</char></note>Μωϋσῆς μὲν εἶπεν<note caller="5" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">3.22 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{B} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">εἶπεν </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">74</char> ℵ A B C 81 307 453 610 1175 1678 2818 <char style="it">l</char> 60 it<char style="add">ar, c, dem, ph, ro, w</char> vg syr<char style="add">p</char> cop<char style="add">bo</char> arm<char style="add">mss</char> geo Ambrose Chromatius ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">πρὸς τοὺς πατέρας εἶπεν </char><char style="ft" closed="false">181 614 1409 <char style="it">Byz</char> [P] <char style="it">Lect</char> ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">εἶπεν πρὸς τοὺς πατέρας </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Ψ 945 1739 1891 Chrysostom ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">εἶπεν πρὸς τοὺς πατέρας ἡμῶν </char><char style="ft" closed="false">D (E </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ὑμῶν</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) 33<char style="add">vid</char> 2344<char style="add">vid</char> it<char style="add">d, (e), gig, h, p</char> vg<char style="add">mss</char> cop<char style="add">sa, meg</char> arm<char style="add">mss</char> eth slav Irenaeus<char style="add">lat</char>; (Greek ms<char style="add">acc. to Bede</char>) DHH</char></note> ὅτι <char style="qt">Προφήτην ὑμῖν ἀναστήσει κύριος ὁ θεὸς ὑμῶν</char><note caller="6" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">3.22 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{C} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ὁ θεὸς ὑμῶν </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ<char style="add">2</char> D 81 181 307 453 610 945 1175 1678 1739 1891 2818 <char style="it">Byz</char><char style="add">pt</char> <char style="it">Lect</char><char style="add">pt, AD</char> it<char style="add">ar, c, d, dem, gig, ph, ro, w</char> vg arm geo slav<char style="add">ms</char> Irenaeus<char style="add">lat</char> Origen<char style="add">gr3/4, lat</char> Chrysostom Severian Cyril; Chromatius ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ὁ θεὸς ἡμῶν </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ* C E Ψ 33 614 1409 2344<char style="add">vid</char> <char style="it">Byz</char><char style="add">pt</char> [P] <char style="it">Lect</char><char style="add">pt</char> it<char style="add">e</char> syr<char style="add">h</char> cop<char style="add">sa<char style="add">mss</char></char> eth slav Origen<char style="add">1/4</char> Ps-Clementines Ps-Justin; Ambrose Gaudentius ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ὁ θεός </char><char style="ft" closed="false">B <char style="it">l</char> 680 <char style="it">l</char> 1178 it<char style="add">h, p</char> cop<char style="add">sa<char style="add">ms</char>, bo</char> Ps-Athanasius Eusebius Titus-Bostra Didymus; Quodvultdeus REB BJ TOB ⫽ <char style="it">omit</char> syr<char style="add">p</char></char></note> <char style="qt">ἐκ τῶν ἀδελφῶν ὑμῶν ὡς ἐμέ· αὐτοῦ ἀκούσεσθε κατὰ πάντα ὅσα ἂν λαλήσῃ</char> πρὸς ὑμᾶς. <verse number="23" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">3.23 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="DEU 18:19">Dt 18.19</ref>; <ref loc="LEV 23:29">Lv 23.29</ref></char></note><char style="qt">ἔσται δὲ πᾶσα ψυχὴ ἥτις ἐὰν μὴ ἀκούσῃ τοῦ προφήτου ἐκείνου ἐξολεθρευθήσεται ἐκ τοῦ λαοῦ.</char> <verse number="24" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">3.24 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 24:27">Lk 24.27</ref></char></note>καὶ πάντες δὲ οἱ προφῆται ἀπὸ Σαμουὴλ καὶ τῶν καθεξῆς ὅσοι ἐλάλησαν καὶ κατήγγειλαν τὰς ἡμέρας ταύτας. <verse number="25" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">3.25 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">Καὶ ἐν … γῆς </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="GEN 22:18">Gn 22.18</ref>; <ref loc="GEN 26:4">26.4</ref> (<ref loc="GEN 12:3">12.3</ref>; <ref loc="GEN 18:18">18.18</ref>; <ref loc="GAL 3:8">Ga 3.8</ref>)</char></note>ὑμεῖς ἐστε οἱ υἱοὶ τῶν προφητῶν καὶ τῆς διαθήκης ἧς διέθετο ὁ θεὸς πρὸς τοὺς πατέρας ὑμῶν<note caller="7" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">3.25 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{C} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ὑμῶν </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">74</char> ℵ<char style="add">2</char> A B E 81 453 945 1175 1739 2344 <char style="it">l</char> 1178 it<char style="add">e</char> vg<char style="add">ww, st</char> cop<char style="add">sa<char style="add">mss</char>, bo<char style="add">mss</char></char> arm<char style="add">mss</char> geo slav<char style="add">ms</char> Irenaeus<char style="add">lat</char> Chrysostom ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἡμῶν </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ* C D Ψ 0165 181 307 610 614 1409 1678 1891 2818 <char style="it">Byz</char> [P] <char style="it">Lect</char> it<char style="add">ar, c, d, dem, gig, h, p, ph, ro, w</char> vg<char style="add">cl</char> syr<char style="add">p, h</char> cop<char style="add">sa<char style="add">mss</char>, bo, meg</char> arm<char style="add">mss</char> eth slav<char style="add">ms</char> Irenaeus<char style="add">lat<char style="add">mss</char></char>; Fulgentius</char></note> λέγων πρὸς Ἀβραάμ, <char style="qt">Καὶ ἐν τῷ σπέρματί σου [ἐν]ευλογηθήσονται πᾶσαι αἱ πατριαὶ τῆς γῆς.</char> <verse number="26" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">3.26 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ὑμῖν πρῶτον … αὐτόν </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 13:46">Ac 13.46</ref>; <ref loc="ROM 1:16">Ro 1.16</ref></char></note>ὑμῖν πρῶτον ἀναστήσας ὁ θεὸς τὸν παῖδα αὐτοῦ ἀπέστειλεν αὐτὸν εὐλογοῦντα ὑμᾶς ἐν τῷ ἀποστρέφειν ἕκαστον ἀπὸ τῶν πονηριῶν ὑμῶν.</para>
  <chapter number="4" style="c" />
  <para style="s">Peter and John before the Council</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">4.1 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">οἱ ἱερεῖς … ἱεροῦ </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="LUK 22:4">Lk 22.4</ref>, <ref loc="LUK 22:52">52</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 5:24">Ac 5.24</ref></char>
    </note>
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">4.1‑2 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">οἱ Σαδδουκαῖοι … νεκρῶν </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="MAT 22:23">Mt 22.23</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 12:18">Mk 12.18</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 20:27">Lk 20.27</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 23:8">Ac 23.8</ref></char>
    </note>Λαλούντων δὲ αὐτῶν πρὸς τὸν λαὸν ἐπέστησαν αὐτοῖς οἱ ἱερεῖς<note caller="1" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">4.1 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{B} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἱερεῖς </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ A D E Ψ 0165 33 81 181 307 453 610 614 945 1175 1409 1678 1739 1891 2344 2818 <char style="it">Byz</char> [P] <char style="it">Lect</char> it<char style="add">ar, c, d, dem, e, h, p, ph, ro, w</char> vg syr<char style="add">p, h</char> cop<char style="add">sa, bo, meg</char> arm<char style="add">mss</char> geo slav Chrysostom ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἀρχιερεῖς </char><char style="ft" closed="false">B C arm<char style="add">mss</char> eth REB ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἱερεῖς καὶ ἀρχιερεῖς </char><char style="ft" closed="false">(<char style="it">but omit</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">καὶ ὁ στρατηγός</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) it<char style="add">gig</char> (Lucifer)</char></note> καὶ ὁ στρατηγὸς τοῦ ἱεροῦ καὶ οἱ Σαδδουκαῖοι, <verse number="2" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">4.2 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">καταγγέλλειν … νεκρῶν </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 4:33">Ac 4.33</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 17:18">17.18</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 26:23">26.23</ref></char></note>διαπονούμενοι διὰ τὸ διδάσκειν αὐτοὺς τὸν λαὸν καὶ καταγγέλλειν ἐν τῷ Ἰησοῦ τὴν ἀνάστασιν τὴν ἐκ νεκρῶν, <verse number="3" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">4.3 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ἐπέβαλον … τήρησιν </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 5:18">Ac 5.18</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ἦν γὰρ ἑσπέρα ἤδη </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 3:1">Ac 3.1</ref></char></note>καὶ ἐπέβαλον αὐτοῖς τὰς χεῖρας καὶ ἔθεντο εἰς τήρησιν εἰς τὴν αὔριον· ἦν γὰρ ἑσπέρα ἤδη. <verse number="4" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">4.4 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 2:41">Ac 2.41</ref>, <ref loc="ACT 2:47">47</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 5:14">5.14</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 6:7">6.7</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 11:21">11.21</ref>, <ref loc="ACT 11:24">24</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 21:20">21.20</ref></char></note>πολλοὶ δὲ τῶν ἀκουσάντων τὸν λόγον ἐπίστευσαν, καὶ ἐγενήθη [ὁ] ἀριθμὸς τῶν ἀνδρῶν [ὡς] χιλιάδες πέντε.</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="5" style="v" />Ἐγένετο δὲ ἐπὶ τὴν αὔριον συναχθῆναι αὐτῶν τοὺς ἄρχοντας καὶ τοὺς πρεσβυτέρους καὶ τοὺς γραμματεῖς ἐν Ἰερουσαλήμ, <verse number="6" style="v" />καὶ Ἅννας ὁ ἀρχιερεὺς καὶ Καϊάφας καὶ Ἰωάννης<note caller="2" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">4.6 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{A} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">Ἰωάννης </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">74</char> ℵ A B 0165 81 307 453 610 1175 1678 2818 it<char style="add">ar, c, dem, h, p<char style="add">mg</char>, ph, ro, w</char> vg syr<char style="add">p, h</char> cop<char style="add">sa, bo, meg</char> arm eth geo slav ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">Ἰωάννην </char><char style="ft" closed="false">E Ψ 33 181 614 945 1409 1739 1891 2344 <char style="it">Byz</char> [P] <char style="it">Lect</char> it<char style="add">e</char> Chrysostom ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">Ἰωνάθας </char><char style="ft" closed="false">D it<char style="add">(d), (gig), (p)</char> (vg<char style="add">ms</char>) Jerome BJ</char></note> καὶ Ἀλέξανδρος καὶ ὅσοι ἦσαν ἐκ γένους ἀρχιερατικοῦ, <verse number="7" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">4.7 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">Ἐν ποίᾳ δυνάμει … ὑμεῖς </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 21:23">Mt 21.23</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 11:28">Mk 11.28</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 20:2">Lk 20.2</ref></char></note>καὶ στήσαντες αὐτοὺς ἐν τῷ μέσῳ ἐπυνθάνοντο, Ἐν ποίᾳ δυνάμει ἢ ἐν ποίῳ ὀνόματι ἐποιήσατε τοῦτο ὑμεῖς; <verse number="8" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">4.8 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">τότε … πλησθεὶς … αὐτούς </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 10:19-20">Mt 10.19‑20</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 13:11">Mk 13.11</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 12:11-12">Lk 12.11‑12</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">πλησθεὶς … ἁγίου </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 6:3">Ac 6.3</ref>, <ref loc="ACT 6:5">5</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 7:55">7.55</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 9:17">9.17</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 11:24">11.24</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 13:9">13.9</ref></char></note>τότε Πέτρος πλησθεὶς πνεύματος ἁγίου εἶπεν πρὸς αὐτούς, Ἄρχοντες τοῦ λαοῦ καὶ πρεσβύτεροι<note caller="3" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">4.8 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{B} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">πρεσβύτεροι </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">74</char> ℵ A B 0165 1175 1409* it<char style="add">ar, c, ph</char> vg cop<char style="add">sa, bo</char> eth Cyril ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">πρεσβύτεροι τοῦ Ἰσραήλ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">D E Ψ 33 181 307 453 610 614 945 1409<char style="add">c</char> 1678 1739 1891 2344 2818 <char style="it">Byz</char> [P] <char style="it">Lect</char> (<char style="it">l</char> 593 </char><char style="fk" closed="false">οἱ πρεσβύτεροι</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) it<char style="add">d, e, gig, h, p<char style="add">(2)</char>, (w)</char> (vg<char style="add">mss</char>) syr<char style="add">p, h</char> cop<char style="add">meg</char> arm geo slav Irenaeus<char style="add">lat</char> Chrysostom; Cyprian Ambrose Greek ms<char style="add">acc. to Bede</char></char></note>, <verse number="9" style="v" />εἰ ἡμεῖς σήμερον ἀνακρινόμεθα ἐπὶ εὐεργεσίᾳ ἀνθρώπου ἀσθενοῦς ἐν τίνι οὗτος σέσωται, <verse number="10" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">4.10 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ἐν τῷ … Ναζωραίου </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 3:6">Ac 3.6</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ὃν ὑμεῖς ἐσταυρώσατε </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 2:36">Ac 2.36</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 5:30">5.30</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 10:39">10.39</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ὃν ὁ … νεκρῶν </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 2:24">Ac 2.24</ref>, <ref loc="ACT 2:32">32</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 3:15">3.15</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 5:30">5.30</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 10:40">10.40</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 13:30">13.30</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 17:31">17.31</ref></char></note>γνωστὸν ἔστω πᾶσιν ὑμῖν καὶ παντὶ τῷ λαῷ Ἰσραὴλ ὅτι ἐν τῷ ὀνόματι Ἰησοῦ Χριστοῦ τοῦ Ναζωραίου ὃν ὑμεῖς ἐσταυρώσατε, ὃν ὁ θεὸς ἤγειρεν ἐκ νεκρῶν, ἐν τούτῳ οὗτος παρέστηκεν ἐνώπιον ὑμῶν ὑγιής<note caller="4" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">4.10 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{A} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ὑγιής </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">74</char> ℵ A B D Ψ 0165 33 181 307 453 610 614 945 1175 1409 1678 1739 1891 2344 2818 <char style="it">Byz</char> [P] <char style="it">Lect</char> it<char style="add">ar, c, d, dem, gig, p, ph, ro, w</char> vg syr<char style="add">p, h</char> cop<char style="add">sa, bo</char> arm eth geo slav Irenaeus<char style="add">lat</char> Athanasius Chrysostom Cyril; Ambrose ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">σήμερον ὑγιής καὶ ἐν ἄλλῳ οὐδενί </char><char style="ft" closed="false">(<char style="it">see</char> <char style="xt"><ref loc="ACT 4:12">4.12</ref>)</char> E it<char style="add">e, (h)</char> (vg<char style="add">mss</char>) (syr<char style="add">h<char style="add">mg</char></char>) (cop<char style="add">meg</char>) (Cyprian) Greek ms<char style="add">acc. to Bede</char> (BJ)</char></note>. <verse number="11" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">4.11 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ὁ λίθος … γωνίας </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="PSA 118:22">Ps 118.22</ref>; <ref loc="MAT 21:42">Mt 21.42</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 12:10">Mk 12.10</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 20:17">Lk 20.17</ref>; <ref loc="1PE 2:4">1 Pe 2.4</ref>, <ref loc="1PE 2:7">7</ref></char></note>οὗτός ἐστιν</para>
  <para style="q1">
    <char style="qt">ὁ λίθος, ὁ ἐξουθενηθεὶς ὑφ᾽</char> ὑμῶν <char style="qt">τῶν οἰκοδόμων,</char></para>
  <para style="q2">
    <char style="qt">ὁ γενόμενος εἰς κεφαλὴν γωνίας.</char></para>
  <para style="m">
    <verse number="12" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">4.12 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">οὐδὲ γὰρ ὄνομα … ἡμᾶς </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="MAT 1:21">Mt 1.21</ref>
      </char>
    </note>καὶ οὐκ ἔστιν ἐν ἄλλῳ οὐδενὶ ἡ σωτηρία<note caller="5" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">4.12 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{A} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">καὶ οὐκ ἔστιν ἐν ἄλλῳ οὐδενὶ ἡ σωτηρία </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">74</char> ℵ A B E Ψ 0165 33 181 (307 453 610 </char><char style="fk" closed="false">οὐδενὶ ἄλλῳ</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) 614 945 1175 1409 (1678 2818 </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἔστιν οὐδενὶ ἄλλῳ</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) 1739 1891 2344 <char style="it">Byz</char> [P] it<char style="add">ar, c, dem, e, gig, p<char style="add">2</char>, ph, ro, w</char> vg syr<char style="add">p, h</char> cop<char style="add">sa, bo, meg</char> arm eth geo slav Didymus<char style="add">dub</char> Chrysostom Cyril ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">καὶ οὐκ ἔστιν ἐν ἄλλῳ οὐδενί </char><char style="ft" closed="false">D it<char style="add">d, p*</char> ⫽ <char style="it">omit</char> it<char style="add">h</char> Irenaeus<char style="add">lat</char>; Cyprian Augustine BJ</char></note>, οὐδὲ γὰρ ὄνομά ἐστιν ἕτερον ὑπὸ τὸν οὐρανὸν τὸ δεδομένον ἐν ἀνθρώποις ἐν ᾧ δεῖ σωθῆναι ἡμᾶς. <verse number="13" style="v" />Θεωροῦντες δὲ τὴν τοῦ Πέτρου παρρησίαν καὶ Ἰωάννου καὶ καταλαβόμενοι ὅτι ἄνθρωποι ἀγράμματοί εἰσιν καὶ ἰδιῶται, ἐθαύμαζον ἐπεγίνωσκόν τε αὐτοὺς ὅτι σὺν τῷ Ἰησοῦ ἦσαν, <verse number="14" style="v" />τόν τε ἄνθρωπον βλέποντες σὺν αὐτοῖς ἑστῶτα τὸν τεθεραπευμένον οὐδὲν εἶχον ἀντειπεῖν. <verse number="15" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">4.15 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 5:34-35">Ac 5.34‑35</ref></char></note>κελεύσαντες δὲ αὐτοὺς ἔξω τοῦ συνεδρίου ἀπελθεῖν συνέβαλλον πρὸς ἀλλήλους <verse number="16" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">4.16 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">Τί … φανερόν </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="JHN 11:47">Jn 11.47</ref></char></note>λέγοντες, Τί ποιήσωμεν τοῖς ἀνθρώποις τούτοις; ὅτι μὲν γὰρ γνωστὸν σημεῖον γέγονεν δι᾽ αὐτῶν πᾶσιν τοῖς κατοικοῦσιν Ἰερουσαλὴμ φανερὸν καὶ οὐ δυνάμεθα ἀρνεῖσθαι· <verse number="17" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">4.17‑18 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 5:28">Ac 5.28</ref></char></note>ἀλλ᾽ ἵνα μὴ ἐπὶ πλεῖον διανεμηθῇ εἰς τὸν λαὸν ἀπειλησώμεθα αὐτοῖς μηκέτι λαλεῖν ἐπὶ τῷ ὀνόματι τούτῳ μηδενὶ ἀνθρώπων. <verse number="18" style="v" />καὶ καλέσαντες αὐτοὺς παρήγγειλαν τὸ καθόλου μὴ φθέγγεσθαι μηδὲ διδάσκειν ἐπὶ τῷ ὀνόματι τοῦ Ἰησοῦ. <verse number="19" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">4.19 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 5:29">Ac 5.29</ref></char></note>ὁ δὲ Πέτρος καὶ Ἰωάννης ἀποκριθέντες εἶπον πρὸς αὐτούς, Εἰ δίκαιόν ἐστιν ἐνώπιον τοῦ θεοῦ ὑμῶν ἀκούειν μᾶλλον ἢ τοῦ θεοῦ, κρίνατε· <verse number="20" style="v" />οὐ δυνάμεθα γὰρ ἡμεῖς ἃ εἴδαμεν καὶ ἠκούσαμεν μὴ λαλεῖν. <verse number="21" style="v" />οἱ δὲ προσαπειλησάμενοι ἀπέλυσαν αὐτούς, μηδὲν εὑρίσκοντες τὸ πῶς κολάσωνται αὐτούς, διὰ τὸν λαόν, ὅτι πάντες ἐδόξαζον τὸν θεὸν ἐπὶ τῷ γεγονότι· <verse number="22" style="v" />ἐτῶν γὰρ ἦν πλειόνων τεσσεράκοντα ὁ ἄνθρωπος ἐφ᾽ ὃν γεγόνει τὸ σημεῖον τοῦτο τῆς ἰάσεως.</para>
  <para style="s">The Believers Pray for Boldness</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="23" style="v" />Ἀπολυθέντες δὲ ἦλθον πρὸς τοὺς ἰδίους καὶ ἀπήγγειλαν ὅσα πρὸς αὐτοὺς οἱ ἀρχιερεῖς καὶ οἱ πρεσβύτεροι εἶπαν. <verse number="24" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">4.24 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ὁ ποιήσας … αὐτοῖς </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="EXO 20:11">Ex 20.11</ref>; <ref loc="PSA 146:6">Ps 146.6</ref></char></note>οἱ δὲ ἀκούσαντες ὁμοθυμαδὸν ἦραν φωνὴν πρὸς τὸν θεὸν καὶ εἶπαν, Δέσποτα, σὺ<note caller="6" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">4.24 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{B} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">σύ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">74</char> ℵ A B 2495 it<char style="add">c, dem, ph, ro, w</char> vg<char style="add">(cl)</char> cop<char style="add">bo</char> (Hilary) (Augustine) ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">σὺ ὁ θεός </char><char style="ft" closed="false">D E Ψ 307 453 610 614 945 1175 1678 1739 1891 2818 <char style="it">Byz</char> [P] <char style="it">Lect</char> it<char style="add">e, gig, p</char> vg<char style="add">mss</char> geo slav Hesychius (Chrysostom); Lucifer ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">σὺ εἶ ὁ θεός </char><char style="ft" closed="false"><char style="it">l</char> 593 <char style="it">l</char> 680 <char style="it">l</char> 1154 <char style="it">l</char> 1443 it<char style="add">d</char> cop<char style="add">sa, meg</char> Irenaeus<char style="add">lat</char> ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">κύριε ὁ θεός </char><char style="ft" closed="false">(<char style="it">see</char> <char style="xt"><ref loc="EXO 20:11">Ex 20.11</ref>; <ref loc="PSA 146:6">Ps 146.6</ref>)</char> 33 181 2344 <char style="it">l</char> 883 (arm) (eth)</char></note> ὁ ποιήσας τὸν οὐρανὸν καὶ τὴν γῆν καὶ τὴν θάλασσαν καὶ πάντα τὰ ἐν αὐτοῖς, <verse number="25" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">4.25‑26 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">Ἱνατί … αὐτοῦ </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="PSA 2:1-2">Ps 2.1‑2</ref></char></note>ὁ τοῦ πατρὸς ἡμῶν διὰ πνεύματος ἁγίου στόματος Δαυὶδ παιδός σου εἰπών<note caller="7" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">4.25 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{C} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ὁ τοῦ πατρὸς ἡμῶν διὰ πνεύματος ἁγίου στόματος Δαυὶδ παιδός σου εἰπών </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">74</char> ℵ A B E Ψ 33 307 453 610 (945 </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ὁ διὰ τοῦ πατρὸς ἡμῶν ἐν πνεύματι ἁγίῳ …</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) 1175 1409<char style="add">vid</char> (1678 <char style="it">omit</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τοῦ … ἡμῶν</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) 1739 1891 2344 2818 <char style="it">l</char> 60 <char style="it">l</char> 1178 it<char style="add">(ar), (c), (dem), e, (gig), (p), (ph), (ro), (w)</char> (vg) (eth) (geo) (Irenaeus<char style="add">lat</char>) Athanasius Hesychius; (Hilary) (Augustine) ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ὅς διὰ πνεύματος ἁγίου διὰ τοῦ στόματος λαλήσας Δαυὶδ παιδός σου </char><char style="ft" closed="false">D (it<char style="add">d</char>) (syr<char style="add">p</char>) (Didymus<char style="add">dub</char>) (REB) ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ὁ διὰ στόματος Δαυὶδ παιδός σου εἰπών </char><char style="ft" closed="false">181 614 <char style="it">Byz</char> [P] <char style="it">Lect</char> (<char style="it">l</char> 165 <char style="it">l</char> 593 </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τοῦ παιδός</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) (it<char style="add">p</char>) (arm) (geo) (slav) Chrysostom</char></note>,</para>
  <para style="q1">
    <char style="qt">Ἱνατί ἐφρύαξαν ἔθνη</char></para>
  <para style="q2">
    <char style="qt">καὶ λαοὶ ἐμελέτησαν κενά;</char></para>
  <para style="q1">
    <verse number="26" style="v" />
    <char style="qt">παρέστησαν οἱ βασιλεῖς τῆς γῆς</char></para>
  <para style="q2">
    <char style="qt">καὶ οἱ ἄρχοντες συνήχθησαν ἐπὶ τὸ αὐτὸ</char></para>
  <para style="q3">
    <char style="qt">κατὰ τοῦ κυρίου καὶ κατὰ τοῦ χριστοῦ αὐτοῦ.</char></para>
  <para style="m">
    <verse number="27" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">4.27 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">τὸν … Ἰησοῦν </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="ACT 3:13">Ac 3.13</ref> </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">ὃν ἔχρισας </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="ISA 61:1">Is 61.1</ref>
      </char>
    </note>συνήχθησαν γὰρ ἐπ᾽ ἀληθείας ἐν τῇ πόλει ταύτῃ ἐπὶ τὸν ἅγιον παῖδά σου Ἰησοῦν ὃν ἔχρισας, Ἡρῴδης τε καὶ Πόντιος Πιλᾶτος σὺν ἔθνεσιν καὶ λαοῖς Ἰσραήλ, <verse number="28" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">4.28 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 2:23">Ac 2.23</ref></char></note>ποιῆσαι ὅσα ἡ χείρ σου καὶ ἡ βουλή [σου] προώρισεν γενέσθαι. <verse number="29" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">4.29 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">μετὰ … λόγον σου </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="EPH 6:19">Eph 6.19</ref></char></note>καὶ τὰ νῦν, κύριε, ἔπιδε ἐπὶ τὰς ἀπειλὰς αὐτῶν καὶ δὸς τοῖς δούλοις σου μετὰ παρρησίας πάσης λαλεῖν τὸν λόγον σου, <verse number="30" style="v" />ἐν τῷ τὴν χεῖρά [σου] ἐκτείνειν σε εἰς ἴασιν καὶ σημεῖα καὶ τέρατα γίνεσθαι διὰ τοῦ ὀνόματος τοῦ ἁγίου παιδός σου Ἰησοῦ. <verse number="31" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">4.31 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ἐπλήσθησαν … πνεύματος </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 2:4">Ac 2.4</ref></char></note>καὶ δεηθέντων αὐτῶν ἐσαλεύθη ὁ τόπος ἐν ᾧ ἦσαν συνηγμένοι, καὶ ἐπλήσθησαν ἅπαντες τοῦ ἁγίου πνεύματος καὶ ἐλάλουν τὸν λόγον τοῦ θεοῦ μετὰ παρρησίας.</para>
  <para style="s">All Things in Common</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="32" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">4.32 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">οὐδὲ … κοινά </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="ACT 2:44">Ac 2.44</ref>
      </char>
    </note>Τοῦ δὲ πλήθους τῶν πιστευσάντων ἦν καρδία καὶ ψυχὴ μία, καὶ οὐδὲ εἷς τι τῶν ὑπαρχόντων αὐτῷ ἔλεγεν ἴδιον εἶναι ἀλλ᾽ ἦν αὐτοῖς ἅπαντα κοινά. <verse number="33" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">4.33 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ἀπεδίδουν … Ἰησοῦ </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 4:2">Ac 4.2</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">χάρις … αὐτούς </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 2:47">Ac 2.47</ref></char></note>καὶ δυνάμει μεγάλῃ ἀπεδίδουν τὸ μαρτύριον οἱ ἀπόστολοι τῆς ἀναστάσεως τοῦ κυρίου Ἰησοῦ<note caller="8" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">4.33 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{C} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τῆς ἀναστάσεως τοῦ κυρίου Ἰησοῦ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">8</char> (B </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τῆς ἀναστάσεως </char><char style="ft" closed="false"><char style="it">after</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">Ἰησοῦ)</char><char style="ft" closed="false">Ψ 181 614 2344 <char style="it">Byz</char> [P] it<char style="add">gig, p, t</char> syr<char style="add">h</char> cop<char style="add">sa</char> arm<char style="add">mss</char> eth Irenaeus<char style="add">lat</char> Orsiesius<char style="add">lat</char>; Augustine ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τῆς ἀναστάσεως Ἰησοῦ Χριστοῦ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">syr<char style="add">p</char> cop<char style="add">bo<char style="add">mss</char></char> ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τῆς ἀναστάσεως Ἰησοῦ Χριστοῦ τοῦ κυρίου </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ A (307 453 610 1678 2818 </char><char style="fk" closed="false">κυρίου ἡμῶν</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) 1175 1409 it<char style="add">ar, c, dem, ro, (w)</char> vg<char style="add">(cl)</char> cop<char style="add">bo<char style="add">(mss)</char></char> (Chrysostom) ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τῆς ἀναστάσεως τοῦ κυρίου Ἰησοῦ Χριστοῦ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">D E 945 1739 1891 <char style="it">l</char> 1178 it<char style="add">d, e, (ph), r</char> (cop<char style="add">meg</char>) arm<char style="add">mss</char> (geo) slav</char></note>, χάρις τε μεγάλη ἦν ἐπὶ πάντας αὐτούς. <verse number="34" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">4.34‑35 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 2:45">Ac 2.45</ref></char></note>οὐδὲ γὰρ ἐνδεής τις ἦν ἐν αὐτοῖς· ὅσοι γὰρ κτήτορες χωρίων ἢ οἰκιῶν ὑπῆρχον, πωλοῦντες ἔφερον τὰς τιμὰς τῶν πιπρασκομένων <verse number="35" style="v" />καὶ ἐτίθουν παρὰ τοὺς πόδας τῶν ἀποστόλων, διεδίδετο δὲ ἑκάστῳ καθότι ἄν τις χρείαν εἶχεν. <verse number="36" style="v" />Ἰωσὴφ δὲ ὁ ἐπικληθεὶς Βαρναβᾶς ἀπὸ τῶν ἀποστόλων, ὅ ἐστιν μεθερμηνευόμενον υἱὸς παρακλήσεως, Λευίτης, Κύπριος τῷ γένει, <verse number="37" style="v" />ὑπάρχοντος αὐτῷ ἀγροῦ πωλήσας ἤνεγκεν τὸ χρῆμα καὶ ἔθηκεν πρὸς τοὺς πόδας τῶν ἀποστόλων.</para>
  <chapter number="5" style="c" />
  <para style="s">Ananias and Sapphira</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" />Ἀνὴρ δέ τις Ἁνανίας ὀνόματι σὺν Σαπφίρῃ τῇ γυναικὶ αὐτοῦ ἐπώλησεν κτῆμα <verse number="2" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5.2 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ἐνέγκας … ἔθηκεν </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 4:34-35">Ac 4.34‑35</ref>, <ref loc="ACT 4:37">37</ref></char></note>καὶ ἐνοσφίσατο ἀπὸ τῆς τιμῆς, συνειδυίης καὶ τῆς γυναικός, καὶ ἐνέγκας μέρος τι παρὰ τοὺς πόδας τῶν ἀποστόλων ἔθηκεν. <verse number="3" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5.3 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ἐπλήρωσεν … σου </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="JHN 13:2">Jn 13.2</ref></char></note>εἶπεν δὲ ὁ Πέτρος, Ἁνανία, διὰ τί ἐπλήρωσεν<note caller="1" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">5.3 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{B} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἐπλήρωσεν </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">8</char> ℵ<char style="add">2</char> A B D E Ψ 0189 33<char style="add">vid</char> 181 307 453 610 614 945 1175 1409 1678 1739 1891 2344 2818 <char style="it">Byz</char> [P] <char style="it">Lect</char> it<char style="add">d, e, gig, p*, r, t</char> syr<char style="add">p, h</char> cop<char style="add">sa, bo, meg</char> arm eth geo slav Origen<char style="add">gr, lat</char> Marcellus Cyril-Jerusalem Gregory-Nyssa Didymus Didymus<char style="add">dub1/2</char> Epiphanius<char style="add">2/4</char> Chrysostom; Cyprian Lucifer Ambrosiaster Ambrose Quodvultdeus Fulgentius Greek ms<char style="add">acc. to Bede</char> ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἐπείρασεν </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">74</char> it<char style="add">ar, c, dem, p<char style="add">2</char>, (ph), ro, w</char> vg Didymus<char style="add">dub1/2</char> Epiphanius<char style="add">2/4</char> Severian ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἐπήρωσεν </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ* ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἐπώρωσεν </char><char style="ft" closed="false">2492</char></note> ὁ Σατανᾶς τὴν καρδίαν σου, ψεύσασθαί σε τὸ πνεῦμα τὸ ἅγιον καὶ νοσφίσασθαι ἀπὸ τῆς τιμῆς τοῦ χωρίου; <verse number="4" style="v" />οὐχὶ μένον σοὶ ἔμενεν καὶ πραθὲν ἐν τῇ σῇ ἐξουσίᾳ ὑπῆρχεν; τί ὅτι ἔθου ἐν τῇ καρδίᾳ σου τὸ πρᾶγμα τοῦτο; οὐκ ἐψεύσω ἀνθρώποις ἀλλὰ τῷ θεῷ. <verse number="5" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5.5 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ἐγένετο … ἀκούοντας </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 2:43">Ac 2.43</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 5:11">5.11</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 19:17">19.17</ref></char></note>ἀκούων δὲ ὁ Ἁνανίας τοὺς λόγους τούτους πεσὼν ἐξέψυξεν, καὶ ἐγένετο φόβος μέγας ἐπὶ πάντας τοὺς ἀκούοντας. <verse number="6" style="v" />ἀναστάντες δὲ οἱ νεώτεροι συνέστειλαν αὐτὸν καὶ ἐξενέγκαντες ἔθαψαν.</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="7" style="v" />Ἐγένετο δὲ ὡς ὡρῶν τριῶν διάστημα καὶ ἡ γυνὴ αὐτοῦ μὴ εἰδυῖα τὸ γεγονὸς εἰσῆλθεν. <verse number="8" style="v" />ἀπεκρίθη δὲ πρὸς αὐτὴν Πέτρος, Εἰπέ μοι, εἰ τοσούτου τὸ χωρίον ἀπέδοσθε; ἡ δὲ εἶπεν, Ναί, τοσούτου. <verse number="9" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5.9 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">πειράσαι … κυρίου </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="1CO 10:9">1 Cor 10.9</ref></char></note>ὁ δὲ Πέτρος πρὸς αὐτήν, Τί ὅτι συνεφωνήθη ὑμῖν πειράσαι τὸ πνεῦμα κυρίου; ἰδοὺ οἱ πόδες τῶν θαψάντων τὸν ἄνδρα σου ἐπὶ τῇ θύρᾳ καὶ ἐξοίσουσίν σε. <verse number="10" style="v" />ἔπεσεν δὲ παραχρῆμα πρὸς τοὺς πόδας αὐτοῦ καὶ ἐξέψυξεν· εἰσελθόντες δὲ οἱ νεανίσκοι εὗρον αὐτὴν νεκρὰν καὶ ἐξενέγκαντες ἔθαψαν πρὸς τὸν ἄνδρα αὐτῆς, <verse number="11" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5.11 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 2:43">Ac 2.43</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 5:5">5.5</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 19:17">19.17</ref></char></note>καὶ ἐγένετο φόβος μέγας ἐφ᾽ ὅλην τὴν ἐκκλησίαν καὶ ἐπὶ πάντας τοὺς ἀκούοντας ταῦτα.</para>
  <para style="s">Many Signs and Wonders Performed</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="12" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">5.12 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">Διὰ … τέρατα πολλά </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="ACT 2:43">Ac 2.43</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 6:8">6.8</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 14:3">14.3</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 15:12">15.12</ref> </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">ἐν τῇ Στοᾷ Σολομῶντος </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="JHN 10:23">Jn 10.23</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 3:11">Ac 3.11</ref></char>
    </note>Διὰ δὲ τῶν χειρῶν τῶν ἀποστόλων ἐγίνετο σημεῖα καὶ τέρατα πολλὰ ἐν τῷ λαῷ. καὶ ἦσαν ὁμοθυμαδὸν ἅπαντες ἐν τῇ Στοᾷ Σολομῶντος, <verse number="13" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5.13 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ἐμεγάλυνεν … λαός </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 2:47">Ac 2.47</ref></char></note>τῶν δὲ λοιπῶν οὐδεὶς ἐτόλμα κολλᾶσθαι αὐτοῖς, ἀλλ᾽ ἐμεγάλυνεν αὐτοὺς ὁ λαός. <verse number="14" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5.14 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 2:41">Ac 2.41</ref>, <ref loc="ACT 2:47">47</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 4:4">4.4</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 6:7">6.7</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 11:21">11.21</ref>, <ref loc="ACT 11:24">24</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 21:20">21.20</ref></char></note>μᾶλλον δὲ προσετίθεντο πιστεύοντες τῷ κυρίῳ, πλήθη ἀνδρῶν τε καὶ γυναικῶν, <verse number="15" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5.15‑16 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MRK 6:56">Mk 6.56</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 19:11-12">Ac 19.11‑12</ref></char></note>ὥστε καὶ εἰς τὰς πλατείας ἐκφέρειν τοὺς ἀσθενεῖς καὶ τιθέναι ἐπὶ κλιναρίων καὶ κραβάττων, ἵνα ἐρχομένου Πέτρου κἂν ἡ σκιὰ ἐπισκιάσῃ τινὶ αὐτῶν. <verse number="16" style="v" />συνήρχετο δὲ καὶ τὸ πλῆθος τῶν πέριξ πόλεων Ἰερουσαλὴμ<note caller="2" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">5.16 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{B} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">Ἰερουσαλήμ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">74</char> ℵ A B 0189 it<char style="add">ar, dem, gig, p, ph, ro, t, w</char> vg syr<char style="add">p, h</char> eth Lucifer ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">εἰς Ἰερουσαλήμ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">D E Ψ 181 307 453 610 614 945 1175 1409 1678 1739 1891 2344 2818 <char style="it">Byz</char> [P] <char style="it">Lect</char> it<char style="add">c, d, e</char> vg<char style="add">mss</char> arm geo slav (Cyril-Jerusalem) Chrysostom</char></note> φέροντες ἀσθενεῖς καὶ ὀχλουμένους ὑπὸ πνευμάτων ἀκαθάρτων, οἵτινες ἐθεραπεύοντο ἅπαντες.</para>
  <para style="s">Persecution of the Apostles</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="17" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">5.17 </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="ACT 4:1">Ac 4.1</ref>, <ref loc="ACT 4:6">6</ref></char>
    </note>Ἀναστὰς δὲ<note caller="3" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">5.17 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{A} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἀναστὰς δέ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">45, 74</char> ℵ A B D Ψ 0189 33 181 307 453 610 614 945 1175 1409 1678 1739 1891 2344 2818 <char style="it">Byz</char> [P] <char style="it">Lect</char> it<char style="add">c, d, dem, gig, ph, ro, w</char> vg syr<char style="add">h</char> cop<char style="add">sa, bo</char> arm geo slav Basil Chrysostom; Lucifer ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">Ἄννας δέ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">(it<char style="add">ar</char> vg<char style="add">ms</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἀναστὰς δὲ Ἄννας</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) it<char style="add">p</char> cop<char style="add">meg</char> eth ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">καὶ ταῦτα βλέπων ἀναστάς </char><char style="ft" closed="false">E it<char style="add">e</char> Greek ms<char style="add">acc. to Bede</char></char></note> ὁ ἀρχιερεὺς καὶ πάντες οἱ σὺν αὐτῷ, ἡ οὖσα αἵρεσις τῶν Σαδδουκαίων, ἐπλήσθησαν ζήλου <verse number="18" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5.18 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 4:3">Ac 4.3</ref></char></note>καὶ ἐπέβαλον τὰς χεῖρας ἐπὶ τοὺς ἀποστόλους καὶ ἔθεντο αὐτοὺς ἐν τηρήσει δημοσίᾳ. <verse number="19" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5.19 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 12:7-10">Ac 12.7‑10</ref></char></note>ἄγγελος δὲ κυρίου διὰ νυκτὸς ἀνοίξας τὰς θύρας τῆς φυλακῆς ἐξαγαγών τε αὐτοὺς εἶπεν, <verse number="20" style="v" />Πορεύεσθε καὶ σταθέντες λαλεῖτε ἐν τῷ ἱερῷ τῷ λαῷ πάντα τὰ ῥήματα τῆς ζωῆς ταύτης. <verse number="21" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5.21 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ἀπέστειλαν … αὐτούς </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 12:19">Ac 12.19</ref></char></note>ἀκούσαντες δὲ εἰσῆλθον ὑπὸ τὸν ὄρθρον εἰς τὸ ἱερὸν καὶ ἐδίδασκον. Παραγενόμενος δὲ ὁ ἀρχιερεὺς καὶ οἱ σὺν αὐτῷ συνεκάλεσαν τὸ συνέδριον καὶ πᾶσαν τὴν γερουσίαν τῶν υἱῶν Ἰσραὴλ καὶ ἀπέστειλαν εἰς τὸ δεσμωτήριον ἀχθῆναι αὐτούς. <verse number="22" style="v" />οἱ δὲ παραγενόμενοι ὑπηρέται οὐχ εὗρον αὐτοὺς ἐν τῇ φυλακῇ· ἀναστρέψαντες δὲ ἀπήγγειλαν <verse number="23" style="v" />λέγοντες ὅτι Τὸ δεσμωτήριον εὕρομεν κεκλεισμένον ἐν πάσῃ ἀσφαλείᾳ καὶ τοὺς φύλακας ἑστῶτας ἐπὶ τῶν θυρῶν, ἀνοίξαντες δὲ ἔσω οὐδένα εὕρομεν. <verse number="24" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5.24 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ὅ … ἀρχιερεῖς </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 22:4">Lk 22.4</ref>, <ref loc="LUK 22:52">52</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 4:1">Ac 4.1</ref></char></note>ὡς δὲ ἤκουσαν τοὺς λόγους τούτους ὅ τε στρατηγὸς τοῦ ἱεροῦ καὶ οἱ ἀρχιερεῖς, διηπόρουν περὶ αὐτῶν τί ἂν γένοιτο τοῦτο. <verse number="25" style="v" />παραγενόμενος δέ τις ἀπήγγειλεν αὐτοῖς ὅτι Ἰδοὺ οἱ ἄνδρες οὓς ἔθεσθε ἐν τῇ φυλακῇ εἰσὶν ἐν τῷ ἱερῷ ἑστῶτες καὶ διδάσκοντες τὸν λαόν. <verse number="26" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5.26 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ἐφοβοῦντο … λαόν </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 14:5">Mt 14.5</ref>; <ref loc="MAT 21:26">21.26</ref>, <ref loc="MAT 21:46">46</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 11:32">Mk 11.32</ref>; <ref loc="MRK 12:12">12.12</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 20:19">Lk 20.19</ref>; <ref loc="LUK 22:2">22.2</ref></char></note>τότε ἀπελθὼν ὁ στρατηγὸς σὺν τοῖς ὑπηρέταις ἦγεν αὐτοὺς οὐ μετὰ βίας, ἐφοβοῦντο γὰρ τὸν λαὸν μὴ λιθασθῶσιν.</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="27" style="v" />Ἀγαγόντες δὲ αὐτοὺς ἔστησαν ἐν τῷ συνεδρίῳ. καὶ ἐπηρώτησεν αὐτοὺς ὁ ἀρχιερεὺς <verse number="28" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5.28 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">μὴ … ὀνόματι τούτῳ </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 4:18">Ac 4.18</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">βούλεσθε … τούτου </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 27:25">Mt 27.25</ref></char></note>λέγων, [Οὐ] παραγγελίᾳ<note caller="4" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">5.28 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{C} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">οὐ παραγγελίᾳ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ<char style="add">2</char> D E (Ψ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">οὐχί</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) 181 307 453 310 614 945 1409 1678 1739 1891 2344 2818 <char style="it">Byz</char> [P] <char style="it">Lect</char> (<char style="it">l</char> 591 <char style="it">l</char> 883 <char style="it">l</char> 1356 </char><char style="fk" closed="false">παραγγελίαν</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) it<char style="add">e, h, p, w</char> syr<char style="add">p, h</char> cop<char style="add">sa<char style="add">mss</char></char> eth arm slav Basil Chrysostom Cyril<char style="add">1/3</char>; Ambrosiaster Greek ms<char style="add">acc. to Bede</char> ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">παραγγελίᾳ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">74</char> ℵ* A B 1175 it<char style="add">ar, c, d, dem, gig, ph, ro</char> vg cop<char style="add">sa<char style="add">ms</char>, bo, meg</char> geo Cyril<char style="add">2/3</char>; Lucifer NIV NRSV REB EU BJ TOB BTI DHH?</char></note> παρηγγείλαμεν ὑμῖν μὴ διδάσκειν ἐπὶ τῷ ὀνόματι τούτῳ, καὶ ἰδοὺ πεπληρώκατε τὴν Ἰερουσαλὴμ τῆς διδαχῆς ὑμῶν καὶ βούλεσθε ἐπαγαγεῖν ἐφ᾽ ἡμᾶς τὸ αἷμα τοῦ ἀνθρώπου τούτου. <verse number="29" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5.29 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 4:19">Ac 4.19</ref></char></note>ἀποκριθεὶς δὲ Πέτρος καὶ οἱ ἀπόστολοι εἶπαν<note caller="5" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">5.29 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{A} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἀποκριθεὶς δὲ Πέτρος καὶ οἱ ἀπόστολοι εἶπαν </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">74</char> ℵ A B E Ψ 33<char style="add">vid</char> 181 (307 453 1409 1678 2818 </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ὁ Πέτρος</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) 610 614 945 1175 1739 1891 2344 <char style="it">Byz</char> [P] <char style="it">Lect</char> (<char style="it">l</char> 883 <char style="it">l</char> 921 <char style="it">l</char> 1021 <char style="it">l</char> 1154 <char style="it">l</char> 1977 <char style="it">l</char><char style="add">AD</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ὁ Πέτρος, </char><char style="ft" closed="false"><char style="it">l</char> 60 <char style="it">l</char> 597 </char><char style="fk" closed="false">οἱ λοιποὶ ἀπόστολοι</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) it<char style="add">ar, c, dem, e, gig, (p), ph, ro, w</char> vg syr<char style="add">h</char> (cop<char style="add">sa, bo, meg</char>) arm (eth) geo (slav) Basil Chrysostom; Lucifer ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ὁ δὲ Πέτρος εἶπεν πρὸς αὐτούς </char><char style="ft" closed="false">D<char style="add">c</char> (syr<char style="add">p</char>) ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ὁ δὲ Πέτρος εἶπεν πρὸς αὐτούς </char><char style="ft" closed="false"><char style="it">but transpose this phrase after</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἀνθρώποις </char><char style="ft" closed="false"><char style="it">[sic]</char> D* it<char style="add">d, (h)</char></char></note>, Πειθαρχεῖν δεῖ θεῷ μᾶλλον ἢ ἀνθρώποις. <verse number="30" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5.30 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ὁ θεὸς … Ἰησοῦν </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 2:24">Ac 2.24</ref>, <ref loc="ACT 2:32">32</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 3:15">3.15</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 4:10">4.10</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 10:40">10.40</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 13:30">13.30</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 17:31">17.31</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ὃν ὑμεῖς διεχειρίσασθε … ἐπὶ ξύλου </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 2:23">Ac 2.23</ref>, <ref loc="ACT 2:36">36</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 3:15">3.15</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 4:10">4.10</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 10:39">10.39</ref></char></note>ὁ θεὸς τῶν πατέρων ἡμῶν ἤγειρεν Ἰησοῦν ὃν ὑμεῖς διεχειρίσασθε κρεμάσαντες ἐπὶ ξύλου· <verse number="31" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5.31 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ἀρχηγὸν καὶ σωτῆρα </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="HEB 2:10">He 2.10</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ὕψωσεν … αὐτοῦ </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ACT 2:33">Ac 2.33</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">τοῦ δοῦναι … ἁμαρτιῶν </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 24:47">Lk 24.47</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 2:38">Ac 2.38</ref></char></note>τοῦτον ὁ θεὸς ἀρχηγὸν καὶ σωτῆρα ὕψωσεν τῇ δεξιᾷ αὐτοῦ [τοῦ] δοῦναι μετάνοιαν τῷ Ἰσραὴλ καὶ ἄφεσιν ἁμαρτιῶν. <verse number="32" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5.32 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ἡμεῖς … μάρτυρες … τούτων </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="LUK 24:48">Lk 24.48</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 15:27">Jn 15.27</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 1:8">Ac 1.8</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 2:32">2.32</ref>; <ref loc="ACT 3:15">3.15</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ἡμεῖς … πνεῦμα τὸ ἅγιον </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="JHN 15:26">Jn 15.26</ref></char></note>καὶ ἡμεῖς ἐσμεν μάρτυρες<note caller="6" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">5.32 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{B} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἐσμεν μάρτυρες </char><char style="ft" closed="false">𝔓<char style="add">74vid</char> ℵ D* 181 614 1175 <char style="it">l</char> 60 <char style="it">l</char> 591 (<char style="it">l</char> 597 </char><char style="fk" closed="false">μὲν μάρτυρες</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) <char style="it">l</char> 680 <char style="it">l</char> 883 <char style="it">l</char> 1441 it<char style="add">ar, c, dem, ph, ro, w</char> vg cop<char style="add">sa, bo, meg</char> arm<char style="add">mss</char> eth Didymus<char style="add">dub</char> ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">μάρτυρές ἐσμεν </char><char style="ft" closed="false">A 1409 it<char style="add">d, gig, h, p<char style="add">2</char></char> vg<char style="add">mss</char> Ps-Vigilius ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἐσμεν αὐτοῦ μάρτυρες </char><char style="ft" closed="false">D<char style="add">2</char> E (Ψ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">μὲν αὐτοῦ μάρτυρές ἐσμεν</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) 307 453 610 1678 2344 2818 <char style="it">Byz</char> [P] <char style="it">Lect</char> it<char style="add">e, (p*)</char> syr<char style="add">h</char> arm<char style="add">mss</char> geo slav Chrysostom ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἐν αὐτῷ ἐσμεν μάρτυρες </char><char style="ft" closed="false">(B <char style="it">omit</char> </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἐσμεν</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) 945 1739 (1891 </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἐσμεν ἐν αὐτῷ</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) cop<char style="add">bo<char style="add">ms</char></char> Irenaeus<char style="add">lat</char></char></note> τῶν ῥημάτων τούτων καὶ τὸ πνεῦμα τὸ ἅγιον ὃ ἔδωκεν ὁ θεὸς τοῖς πειθαρχοῦσιν αὐτῷ.</para>
  <para style="p">
